16 // =================================================================================================
17 // =================================================================================================
18 // =================================================================================================
19 //
20 // The library is heavily influenced by Catch - https://github.com/philsquared/Catch
21 // which uses the Boost Software License - Version 1.0
22 // see here - https://github.com/philsquared/Catch/blob/master/LICENSE.txt
23 //
24 // The concept of subcases (sections in Catch) and expression decomposition are from there.
25 // Some parts of the code are taken directly:
26 // - stringification - the detection of "ostream& operator<<(ostream&, const T&)" and StringMaker<>
27 // - the Approx() helper class for floating point comparison
28 // - colors in the console
29 // - breaking into a debugger
30 // - signal / SEH handling
31 // - timer
32 //
33 // The expression decomposing templates are taken from lest - https://github.com/martinmoene/lest
34 // which uses the Boost Software License - Version 1.0
35 // see here - https://github.com/martinmoene/lest/blob/master/LICENSE.txt
36 //
37 // The type list and the foreach algorithm on it for C++98 are taken from Loki
38 // - http://loki-lib.sourceforge.net/
39 // - https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Loki_%28C%2B%2B%29
40 // - https://github.com/snaewe/loki-lib
41 // which uses the MIT Software License
42 //

560 // static assert macro - because of the c++98 support requires that the message is an
561 // identifier (no spaces and not a C string) - example without quotes: I_am_a_message
562 // taken from here: http://stackoverflow.com/a/1980156/3162383
563 #ifdef DOCTEST_CONFIG_WITH_STATIC_ASSERT
564 #define DOCTEST_STATIC_ASSERT(expression, message) static_assert(expression, #message)
565 #else // DOCTEST_CONFIG_WITH_STATIC_ASSERT
566 #define DOCTEST_STATIC_ASSERT(expression, message) \
567  struct DOCTEST_CAT(__static_assertion_at_line_, __LINE__) \
568  { \
569  doctest::detail::static_assert_impl::StaticAssertion<static_cast<bool>((expression))> \
570  DOCTEST_CAT(DOCTEST_CAT(DOCTEST_CAT(STATIC_ASSERTION_FAILED_AT_LINE_, __LINE__), \
571  _), \
572  message); \
573  }; \
574  typedef doctest::detail::static_assert_impl::StaticAssertionTest<static_cast<int>( \
575  sizeof(DOCTEST_CAT(__static_assertion_at_line_, __LINE__)))> \
576  DOCTEST_CAT(__static_assertion_test_at_line_, __LINE__)
577 #endif // DOCTEST_CONFIG_WITH_STATIC_ASSERT

615  m_may_fail = false;

640 namespace doctest
641 {
642 // A 24 byte string class (can be as small as 17 for x64 and 13 for x86) that can hold strings with length
643 // of up to 23 chars on the stack before going on the heap - the last byte of the buffer is used for:
644 // - "is small" bit - the highest bit - if "0" then it is small - otherwise its "1" (128)
645 // - if small - capacity left before going on the heap - using the lowest 5 bits
646 // - if small - 2 bits are left unused - the second and third highest ones
647 // - if small - acts as a null terminator if strlen() is 23 (24 including the null terminator)
648 // and the "is small" bit remains "0" ("as well as the capacity left") so its OK
649 // Idea taken from this lecture about the string implementation of facebook/folly - fbstring
650 // https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kPR8h4-qZdk
651 // TODO:
652 // - optimizations - like not deleting memory unnecessarily in operator= and etc.
653 // - resize/reserve/clear
654 // - substr
655 // - replace
656 // - back/front
657 // - iterator stuff
658 // - find & friends
659 // - push_back/pop_back
660 // - assign/insert/erase
661 // - relational operators as free functions - taking const char* as one of the params
662 class DOCTEST_INTERFACE String
663 {
664  static const unsigned len = 24;
665  static const unsigned last = len - 1;
666 
667  struct view // len should be more than sizeof(view) - because of the final byte for flags
668  {
669  char* ptr;
670  unsigned size;
671  unsigned capacity;
672  };
673 
674  union
675  {
676  char buf[len];
677  view data;
678  };
679 
680  void copy(const String& other);
681 
682  void setOnHeap() { *reinterpret_cast<unsigned char*>(&buf[last]) = 128; }
683  void setLast(unsigned in = last) { buf[last] = char(in); }
684 
685 public:
686  String() {
687  buf[0] = '\0';
688  setLast();
689  }
690 
691  String(const char* in);
692 
693  String(const String& other) { copy(other); }
694 
695  ~String() {
696  if(!isOnStack())
697  delete[] data.ptr;
698  }
699 
700  // GCC 4.9/5/6 report Wstrict-overflow when optimizations are ON and it got inlined in the vector class somewhere...
701  // see commit 574ef95f0cd379118be5011704664e4b5351f1e0 and build https://travis-ci.org/onqtam/doctest/builds/230671611
702  DOCTEST_NOINLINE String& operator=(const String& other) {
703  if(this != &other) {
704  if(!isOnStack())
705  delete[] data.ptr;
706 
707  copy(other);
708  }
709 
710  return *this;
711  }
712  String& operator+=(const String& other);
713 
714  String operator+(const String& other) const { return String(*this) += other; }
715 
716 #ifdef DOCTEST_CONFIG_WITH_RVALUE_REFERENCES
717  String(String&& other);
718  String& operator=(String&& other);
719 #endif // DOCTEST_CONFIG_WITH_RVALUE_REFERENCES
720 
721  bool isOnStack() const { return (buf[last] & 128) == 0; }
722 
723  char operator[](unsigned i) const { return const_cast<String*>(this)->operator[](i); } // NOLINT
724  char& operator[](unsigned i) {
725  if(isOnStack())
726  return reinterpret_cast<char*>(buf)[i];
727  return data.ptr[i];
728  }
729 
730  const char* c_str() const { return const_cast<String*>(this)->c_str(); } // NOLINT
731  char* c_str() {
732  if(isOnStack())
733  return reinterpret_cast<char*>(buf);
734  return data.ptr;
735  }
736 
737  unsigned size() const {
738  if(isOnStack())
739  return last - (unsigned(buf[last]) & 31); // using "last" would work only if "len" is 32
740  return data.size;
741  }
742 
743  unsigned capacity() const {
744  if(isOnStack())
745  return len;
746  return data.capacity;
747  }
748 
749  int compare(const char* other, bool no_case = false) const;
750  int compare(const String& other, bool no_case = false) const;
751 };
752 
753 // clang-format off
754 inline bool operator==(const String& lhs, const String& rhs) { return lhs.compare(rhs) == 0; }
755 inline bool operator!=(const String& lhs, const String& rhs) { return lhs.compare(rhs) != 0; }
756 inline bool operator< (const String& lhs, const String& rhs) { return lhs.compare(rhs) < 0; }
757 inline bool operator> (const String& lhs, const String& rhs) { return lhs.compare(rhs) > 0; }
758 inline bool operator<=(const String& lhs, const String& rhs) { return (lhs != rhs) ? lhs.compare(rhs) < 0 : true; }
759 inline bool operator>=(const String& lhs, const String& rhs) { return (lhs != rhs) ? lhs.compare(rhs) > 0 : true; }
760 // clang-format on
761 
762 DOCTEST_INTERFACE std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& stream, const String& in);

864  class NullType
865  {
866  };
867 
868  template <class T, class U>
869  struct Typelist
870  {
871  typedef T Head;
872  typedef U Tail;
873  };
874 
875  // type of recursive function
876  template <class TList, class Callable>
877  struct ForEachType;
878 
879  // Recursion rule
880  template <class Head, class Tail, class Callable>
881  struct ForEachType<Typelist<Head, Tail>, Callable> : public ForEachType<Tail, Callable>
882  {
883  enum
884  {
885  value = 1 + ForEachType<Tail, Callable>::value
886  };
887 
888  explicit ForEachType(Callable& callable)
889  : ForEachType<Tail, Callable>(callable) {
890 #if DOCTEST_MSVC && DOCTEST_MSVC < DOCTEST_COMPILER(19, 10, 0)
891  callable.operator()<value, Head>();
892 #else // MSVC
893  callable.template operator()<value, Head>();
894 #endif // MSVC
895  }
896  };
897 
898  // Recursion end
899  template <class Head, class Callable>
900  struct ForEachType<Typelist<Head, NullType>, Callable>
901  {
902  public:
903  enum
904  {
905  value = 0
906  };
907 
908  explicit ForEachType(Callable& callable) {
909 #if DOCTEST_MSVC && DOCTEST_MSVC < DOCTEST_COMPILER(19, 10, 0)
910  callable.operator()<value, Head>();
911 #else // MSVC
912  callable.template operator()<value, Head>();
913 #endif // MSVC
914  }
915  };
916 
917  template <typename T>
918  const char* type_to_string() {
919  return "<>";
920  }
921 } // namespace detail

1028 class DOCTEST_INTERFACE Approx
1029 {
1030 public:
1031  explicit Approx(double value);
1032 
1033  Approx operator()(double value) const {
1034  Approx approx(value);
1035  approx.epsilon(m_epsilon);
1036  approx.scale(m_scale);
1037  return approx;
1038  }
1039 
1040 #ifdef DOCTEST_CONFIG_INCLUDE_TYPE_TRAITS
1041  template <typename T>
1042  explicit Approx(const T& value,
1043  typename detail::enable_if<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>::type* =
1044  static_cast<T*>(detail::getNull())) {
1045  *this = Approx(static_cast<double>(value));
1046  }
1047 #endif // DOCTEST_CONFIG_INCLUDE_TYPE_TRAITS
1048 
1049  // clang-format off
1050  // overloads for double - the first one is necessary as it is in the implementation part of doctest
1051  // as for the others - keeping them for potentially faster compile times
1052  DOCTEST_INTERFACE friend bool operator==(double lhs, Approx const& rhs);
1053  friend bool operator==(Approx const& lhs, double rhs) { return operator==(rhs, lhs); }
1054  friend bool operator!=(double lhs, Approx const& rhs) { return !operator==(lhs, rhs); }
1055  friend bool operator!=(Approx const& lhs, double rhs) { return !operator==(rhs, lhs); }
1056  friend bool operator<=(double lhs, Approx const& rhs) { return lhs < rhs.m_value || lhs == rhs; }
1057  friend bool operator<=(Approx const& lhs, double rhs) { return lhs.m_value < rhs || lhs == rhs; }
1058  friend bool operator>=(double lhs, Approx const& rhs) { return lhs > rhs.m_value || lhs == rhs; }
1059  friend bool operator>=(Approx const& lhs, double rhs) { return lhs.m_value > rhs || lhs == rhs; }
1060  friend bool operator< (double lhs, Approx const& rhs) { return lhs < rhs.m_value && lhs != rhs; }
1061  friend bool operator< (Approx const& lhs, double rhs) { return lhs.m_value < rhs && lhs != rhs; }
1062  friend bool operator> (double lhs, Approx const& rhs) { return lhs > rhs.m_value && lhs != rhs; }
1063  friend bool operator> (Approx const& lhs, double rhs) { return lhs.m_value > rhs && lhs != rhs; }
1064 
1065 #ifdef DOCTEST_CONFIG_INCLUDE_TYPE_TRAITS
1066 #define DOCTEST_APPROX_PREFIX \
1067  template <typename T> friend typename detail::enable_if<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value, bool>::type
1068 
1069  DOCTEST_APPROX_PREFIX operator==(const T& lhs, const Approx& rhs) { return operator==(double(lhs), rhs); }
1070  DOCTEST_APPROX_PREFIX operator==(const Approx& lhs, const T& rhs) { return operator==(rhs, lhs); }
1071  DOCTEST_APPROX_PREFIX operator!=(const T& lhs, const Approx& rhs) { return !operator==(lhs, rhs); }
1072  DOCTEST_APPROX_PREFIX operator!=(const Approx& lhs, const T& rhs) { return !operator==(rhs, lhs); }
1073  DOCTEST_APPROX_PREFIX operator<=(const T& lhs, const Approx& rhs) { return double(lhs) < rhs.m_value || lhs == rhs; }
1074  DOCTEST_APPROX_PREFIX operator<=(const Approx& lhs, const T& rhs) { return lhs.m_value < double(rhs) || lhs == rhs; }
1075  DOCTEST_APPROX_PREFIX operator>=(const T& lhs, const Approx& rhs) { return double(lhs) > rhs.m_value || lhs == rhs; }
1076  DOCTEST_APPROX_PREFIX operator>=(const Approx& lhs, const T& rhs) { return lhs.m_value > double(rhs) || lhs == rhs; }
1077  DOCTEST_APPROX_PREFIX operator< (const T& lhs, const Approx& rhs) { return double(lhs) < rhs.m_value && lhs != rhs; }
1078  DOCTEST_APPROX_PREFIX operator< (const Approx& lhs, const T& rhs) { return lhs.m_value < double(rhs) && lhs != rhs; }
1079  DOCTEST_APPROX_PREFIX operator> (const T& lhs, const Approx& rhs) { return double(lhs) > rhs.m_value && lhs != rhs; }
1080  DOCTEST_APPROX_PREFIX operator> (const Approx& lhs, const T& rhs) { return lhs.m_value > double(rhs) && lhs != rhs; }
1081 #undef DOCTEST_APPROX_PREFIX
1082 #endif // DOCTEST_CONFIG_INCLUDE_TYPE_TRAITS
1083 
1084  // clang-format on
1085 
1086  Approx& epsilon(double newEpsilon) {
1087  m_epsilon = newEpsilon;
1088  return *this;
1089  }
1090 
1091 #ifdef DOCTEST_CONFIG_INCLUDE_TYPE_TRAITS

1094  const T& newEpsilon) {
1095  m_epsilon = static_cast<double>(newEpsilon);
1096  return *this;
1097  }
1098 #endif // DOCTEST_CONFIG_INCLUDE_TYPE_TRAITS

1100  Approx& scale(double newScale) {
1101  m_scale = newScale;
1102  return *this;
1103  }
1104 
1105 #ifdef DOCTEST_CONFIG_INCLUDE_TYPE_TRAITS

1108  const T& newScale) {
1109  m_scale = static_cast<double>(newScale);
1110  return *this;
1111  }
1112 #endif // DOCTEST_CONFIG_INCLUDE_TYPE_TRAITS
1113 
1114  String toString() const;
1115 
1116 private:

1118  double m_scale;

1120 };

1389 #define DOCTEST_COMPARISON_RETURN_TYPE bool
1390 #else // DOCTEST_CONFIG_TREAT_CHAR_STAR_AS_STRING
1391 #define DOCTEST_COMPARISON_RETURN_TYPE typename enable_if<can_use_op<L>::value || can_use_op<R>::value, bool>::type
1392  inline bool eq(const char* lhs, const char* rhs) { return String(lhs) == String(rhs); }
1393  inline bool ne(const char* lhs, const char* rhs) { return String(lhs) != String(rhs); }
1394  inline bool lt(const char* lhs, const char* rhs) { return String(lhs) < String(rhs); }
1395  inline bool gt(const char* lhs, const char* rhs) { return String(lhs) > String(rhs); }
1396  inline bool le(const char* lhs, const char* rhs) { return String(lhs) <= String(rhs); }
1397  inline bool ge(const char* lhs, const char* rhs) { return String(lhs) >= String(rhs); }
1398 #endif // DOCTEST_CONFIG_TREAT_CHAR_STAR_AS_STRING

1400  template <typename L, typename R> DOCTEST_COMPARISON_RETURN_TYPE eq(const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(L) lhs, const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(R) rhs) { return lhs == rhs; }
1401  template <typename L, typename R> DOCTEST_COMPARISON_RETURN_TYPE ne(const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(L) lhs, const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(R) rhs) { return lhs != rhs; }
1402  template <typename L, typename R> DOCTEST_COMPARISON_RETURN_TYPE lt(const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(L) lhs, const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(R) rhs) { return lhs < rhs; }
1403  template <typename L, typename R> DOCTEST_COMPARISON_RETURN_TYPE gt(const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(L) lhs, const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(R) rhs) { return lhs > rhs; }
1404  template <typename L, typename R> DOCTEST_COMPARISON_RETURN_TYPE le(const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(L) lhs, const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(R) rhs) { return lhs <= rhs; }
1405  template <typename L, typename R> DOCTEST_COMPARISON_RETURN_TYPE ge(const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(L) lhs, const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(R) rhs) { return lhs >= rhs; }

1409 #define DOCTEST_CMP_EQ(l, r) l == r
1410 #define DOCTEST_CMP_NE(l, r) l != r
1411 #define DOCTEST_CMP_GT(l, r) l > r
1412 #define DOCTEST_CMP_LT(l, r) l < r
1413 #define DOCTEST_CMP_GE(l, r) l >= r
1414 #define DOCTEST_CMP_LE(l, r) l <= r
1415 #else // DOCTEST_CONFIG_TREAT_CHAR_STAR_AS_STRING
1416 #define DOCTEST_CMP_EQ(l, r) eq(l, r)
1417 #define DOCTEST_CMP_NE(l, r) ne(l, r)
1418 #define DOCTEST_CMP_GT(l, r) gt(l, r)
1419 #define DOCTEST_CMP_LT(l, r) lt(l, r)
1420 #define DOCTEST_CMP_GE(l, r) ge(l, r)
1421 #define DOCTEST_CMP_LE(l, r) le(l, r)
1422 #endif // DOCTEST_CONFIG_TREAT_CHAR_STAR_AS_STRING

1424 #define DOCTEST_DO_BINARY_EXPRESSION_COMPARISON(op, op_str, op_macro) \
1425  template <typename R> \
1426  DOCTEST_NOINLINE Result operator op(const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(R) rhs) { \
1427  bool res = op_macro(lhs, rhs); \
1428  if(m_assert_type & assertType::is_false) \
1429  res = !res; \
1430  if(!res || doctest::detail::getTestsContextState()->success) \
1431  return Result(res, stringifyBinaryExpr(lhs, op_str, rhs)); \
1432  return Result(res); \
1433  }
1434 
1435 #define DOCTEST_FORBIT_EXPRESSION(op) \
1436  template <typename R> \
1437  Expression_lhs& operator op(const R&) { \
1438  DOCTEST_STATIC_ASSERT(deferred_false<R>::value, \
1439  Expression_Too_Complex_Please_Rewrite_As_Binary_Comparison); \
1440  return *this; \
1441  }
1442 
1443  template <typename L>
1444  // cppcheck-suppress copyCtorAndEqOperator
1445  struct Expression_lhs
1446  {
1447  L lhs;
1448  assertType::Enum m_assert_type;
1449 
1450  explicit Expression_lhs(L in, assertType::Enum assert_type)
1451  : lhs(in)
1452  , m_assert_type(assert_type) {}
1453 
1454  DOCTEST_NOINLINE operator Result() {
1455  bool res = !!lhs;
1456  if(m_assert_type & assertType::is_false)
1457  res = !res;
1458 
1459  if(!res || getTestsContextState()->success)
1460  return Result(res, toString(lhs));
1461  return Result(res);
1462  }
1463 
1464  // clang-format off
1465  DOCTEST_DO_BINARY_EXPRESSION_COMPARISON(==, " == ", DOCTEST_CMP_EQ)
1466  DOCTEST_DO_BINARY_EXPRESSION_COMPARISON(!=, " != ", DOCTEST_CMP_NE)
1467  DOCTEST_DO_BINARY_EXPRESSION_COMPARISON(>, " > ", DOCTEST_CMP_GT)
1468  DOCTEST_DO_BINARY_EXPRESSION_COMPARISON(<, " < ", DOCTEST_CMP_LT)
1469  DOCTEST_DO_BINARY_EXPRESSION_COMPARISON(>=, " >= ", DOCTEST_CMP_GE)
1470  DOCTEST_DO_BINARY_EXPRESSION_COMPARISON(<=, " <= ", DOCTEST_CMP_LE)
1471  // clang-format on
1472 
1473  // forbidding some expressions based on this table: http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/operator_precedence
1474  DOCTEST_FORBIT_EXPRESSION(&)
1475  DOCTEST_FORBIT_EXPRESSION (^)
1476  DOCTEST_FORBIT_EXPRESSION(|)
1477  DOCTEST_FORBIT_EXPRESSION(&&)
1478  DOCTEST_FORBIT_EXPRESSION(||)
1479  DOCTEST_FORBIT_EXPRESSION(=)
1480  DOCTEST_FORBIT_EXPRESSION(+=)
1481  DOCTEST_FORBIT_EXPRESSION(-=)
1482  DOCTEST_FORBIT_EXPRESSION(*=)
1483  DOCTEST_FORBIT_EXPRESSION(/=)
1484  DOCTEST_FORBIT_EXPRESSION(%=)
1485  DOCTEST_FORBIT_EXPRESSION(<<=)
1486  DOCTEST_FORBIT_EXPRESSION(>>=)
1487  DOCTEST_FORBIT_EXPRESSION(&=)
1488  DOCTEST_FORBIT_EXPRESSION(^=)
1489  DOCTEST_FORBIT_EXPRESSION(|=)
1490  // these 2 are unfortunate because they should be allowed - they have higher precedence over the comparisons, but the
1491  // ExpressionDecomposer class uses the left shift operator to capture the left operand of the binary expression...
1492  DOCTEST_FORBIT_EXPRESSION(<<)
1493  DOCTEST_FORBIT_EXPRESSION(>>)
1494  };

1497 
1498  DOCTEST_CLANG_SUPPRESS_WARNING_POP
1499  DOCTEST_MSVC_SUPPRESS_WARNING_POP
1500  DOCTEST_GCC_SUPPRESS_WARNING_POP

1504  struct ExpressionDecomposer
1505  {
1506  assertType::Enum m_assert_type;
1507 
1508  ExpressionDecomposer(assertType::Enum assert_type)
1509  : m_assert_type(assert_type) {}
1510 
1511  // The right operator for capturing expressions is "<=" instead of "<<" (based on the operator precedence table)
1512  // but then there will be warnings from GCC about "-Wparentheses" and since "_Pragma()" is problematic this will stay for now...
1513  // https://github.com/philsquared/Catch/issues/870
1514  // https://github.com/philsquared/Catch/issues/565
1515  template <typename L>
1516  Expression_lhs<const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(L)> operator<<(const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(L) operand) {
1517  return Expression_lhs<const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(L)>(operand, m_assert_type);
1518  }
1519  };

1593  namespace binaryAssertComparison
1594  {
1595  enum Enum
1596  {
1597  eq = 0,

1600  lt,
1601  ge,

1606  // clang-format off
1607  template <int, class L, class R> struct RelationalComparator { bool operator()(const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(L), const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(R) ) const { return false; } };
1608  template <class L, class R> struct RelationalComparator<0, L, R> { bool operator()(const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(L) lhs, const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(R) rhs) const { return eq(lhs, rhs); } };
1609  template <class L, class R> struct RelationalComparator<1, L, R> { bool operator()(const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(L) lhs, const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(R) rhs) const { return ne(lhs, rhs); } };
1610  template <class L, class R> struct RelationalComparator<2, L, R> { bool operator()(const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(L) lhs, const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(R) rhs) const { return gt(lhs, rhs); } };
1611  template <class L, class R> struct RelationalComparator<3, L, R> { bool operator()(const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(L) lhs, const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(R) rhs) const { return lt(lhs, rhs); } };
1612  template <class L, class R> struct RelationalComparator<4, L, R> { bool operator()(const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(L) lhs, const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(R) rhs) const { return ge(lhs, rhs); } };
1613  template <class L, class R> struct RelationalComparator<5, L, R> { bool operator()(const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(L) lhs, const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(R) rhs) const { return le(lhs, rhs); } };

1631  const char* exception_type = "");

1637  template <int comparison, typename L, typename R>
1638  DOCTEST_NOINLINE void binary_assert(const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(L) lhs,
1639  const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(R) rhs) {
1640  m_result.m_passed = RelationalComparator<comparison, L, R>()(lhs, rhs);
1641  if(!m_result.m_passed || getTestsContextState()->success)
1642  m_result.m_decomposition = stringifyBinaryExpr(lhs, ", ", rhs);
1643  }
1644 
1645  template <typename L>
1646  DOCTEST_NOINLINE void unary_assert(const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(L) val) {
1647  m_result.m_passed = !!val;
1648 
1649  if(m_assert_type & assertType::is_false)
1650  m_result.m_passed = !m_result.m_passed;
1651 
1652  if(!m_result.m_passed || getTestsContextState()->success)
1653  m_result.m_decomposition = toString(val);
1654  }
1655 
1656  void unexpectedExceptionOccurred();
1657 
1658  bool log();
1659  void react() const;
1660  };

1662  namespace assertAction
1663  {
1664  enum Enum
1665  {
1666  nothing = 0,
1667  dbgbreak = 1,
1668  shouldthrow = 2
1669  };
1670  } // namespace assertAction
1671 
1672  template <int comparison, typename L, typename R>
1673  DOCTEST_NOINLINE int fast_binary_assert(assertType::Enum assert_type, const char* file,
1674  int line, const char* expr,
1675  const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(L) lhs,
1676  const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(R) rhs) {
1677  ResultBuilder rb(assert_type, file, line, expr);
1678 
1679  rb.m_result.m_passed = RelationalComparator<comparison, L, R>()(lhs, rhs);
1680 
1681  if(!rb.m_result.m_passed || getTestsContextState()->success)
1682  rb.m_result.m_decomposition = stringifyBinaryExpr(lhs, ", ", rhs);
1683 
1684  int res = 0;
1685 
1686  if(rb.log())
1687  res |= assertAction::dbgbreak;
1688 
1689  if(rb.m_failed && checkIfShouldThrow(assert_type))
1690  res |= assertAction::shouldthrow;
1691 
1692 #ifdef DOCTEST_CONFIG_SUPER_FAST_ASSERTS
1693  // #########################################################################################
1694  // IF THE DEBUGGER BREAKS HERE - GO 1 LEVEL UP IN THE CALLSTACK TO SEE THE FAILING ASSERTION
1695  // THIS IS THE EFFECT OF HAVING 'DOCTEST_CONFIG_SUPER_FAST_ASSERTS' DEFINED
1696  // #########################################################################################
1697  if(res & assertAction::dbgbreak)
1698  DOCTEST_BREAK_INTO_DEBUGGER();
1699  fastAssertThrowIfFlagSet(res);
1700 #endif // DOCTEST_CONFIG_SUPER_FAST_ASSERTS
1701 
1702  return res;
1703  }
1704 
1705  template <typename L>
1706  DOCTEST_NOINLINE int fast_unary_assert(assertType::Enum assert_type, const char* file, int line,
1707  const char* val_str, const DOCTEST_REF_WRAP(L) val) {
1708  ResultBuilder rb(assert_type, file, line, val_str);
1709 
1710  rb.m_result.m_passed = !!val;
1711 
1712  if(assert_type & assertType::is_false)
1713  rb.m_result.m_passed = !rb.m_result.m_passed;
1714 
1715  if(!rb.m_result.m_passed || getTestsContextState()->success)
1716  rb.m_result.m_decomposition = toString(val);
1717 
1718  int res = 0;
1719 
1720  if(rb.log())
1721  res |= assertAction::dbgbreak;
1722 
1723  if(rb.m_failed && checkIfShouldThrow(assert_type))
1724  res |= assertAction::shouldthrow;
1725 
1726 #ifdef DOCTEST_CONFIG_SUPER_FAST_ASSERTS
1727  // #########################################################################################
1728  // IF THE DEBUGGER BREAKS HERE - GO 1 LEVEL UP IN THE CALLSTACK TO SEE THE FAILING ASSERTION
1729  // THIS IS THE EFFECT OF HAVING 'DOCTEST_CONFIG_SUPER_FAST_ASSERTS' DEFINED
1730  // #########################################################################################
1731  if(res & assertAction::dbgbreak)
1732  DOCTEST_BREAK_INTO_DEBUGGER();
1733  fastAssertThrowIfFlagSet(res);
1734 #endif // DOCTEST_CONFIG_SUPER_FAST_ASSERTS
1735 
1736  return res;
1737  }

1739  struct DOCTEST_INTERFACE IExceptionTranslator

1745  template <typename T>
1746  class ExceptionTranslator : public IExceptionTranslator
1747  {
1748  public:
1749  explicit ExceptionTranslator(String (*translateFunction)(T))
1750  : m_translateFunction(translateFunction) {}
1751 
1752  bool translate(String& res) const {
1753 #ifndef DOCTEST_CONFIG_NO_EXCEPTIONS
1754  try {
1755  throw;
1756  // cppcheck-suppress catchExceptionByValue
1757  } catch(T ex) { // NOLINT
1758  res = m_translateFunction(ex);
1759  return true;
1760  } catch(...) {}
1761 #endif // DOCTEST_CONFIG_NO_EXCEPTIONS
1762  ((void)res); // to silence -Wunused-parameter
1763  return false;
1764  }
1765 
1766  protected:
1767  String (*m_translateFunction)(T);
1768  };

1844  // cppcheck-suppress copyCtorAndEqOperator
1845  class ContextBuilder
1846  {
1847  friend class ContextScope;
1848 
1849  struct ICapture
1850  {
1851  virtual ~ICapture() {}
1852  virtual void toStream(std::ostream*) const = 0;
1853  };
1854 
1855  template <typename T>
1856  struct Capture : ICapture
1857  {
1858  const T* capture;
1859 
1860  explicit Capture(const T* in)
1861  : capture(in) {}
1862  virtual void toStream(std::ostream* stream) const { // override
1863  detail::toStream(stream, *capture);
1864  }
1865  };
1866 
1867  struct Chunk
1868  {
1869  char buf[sizeof(Capture<char>)] DOCTEST_ALIGNMENT(
1870  2 * sizeof(void*)); // place to construct a Capture<T>
1871  };
1872 
1873  struct Node
1874  {
1875  Chunk chunk;
1876  Node* next;
1877  };
1878 
1879  Chunk stackChunks[DOCTEST_CONFIG_NUM_CAPTURES_ON_STACK];
1880  int numCaptures;
1881  Node* head;
1882  Node* tail;
1883 
1884  void build(std::ostream* stream) const {
1885  int curr = 0;
1886  // iterate over small buffer
1887  while(curr < numCaptures && curr < DOCTEST_CONFIG_NUM_CAPTURES_ON_STACK)
1888  reinterpret_cast<const ICapture*>(stackChunks[curr++].buf)->toStream(stream);
1889  // iterate over list
1890  Node* curr_elem = head;
1891  while(curr < numCaptures) {
1892  reinterpret_cast<const ICapture*>(curr_elem->chunk.buf)->toStream(stream);
1893  curr_elem = curr_elem->next;
1894  ++curr;
1895  }
1896  }
1897 
1898  // steal the contents of the other - acting as a move constructor...
1899  DOCTEST_NOINLINE ContextBuilder(ContextBuilder& other)
1900  : numCaptures(other.numCaptures)
1901  , head(other.head)
1902  , tail(other.tail) {
1903  other.numCaptures = 0;
1904  other.head = 0;
1905  other.tail = 0;
1906  my_memcpy(stackChunks, other.stackChunks,
1907  unsigned(int(sizeof(Chunk)) * DOCTEST_CONFIG_NUM_CAPTURES_ON_STACK));
1908  }
1909 
1910  ContextBuilder& operator=(const ContextBuilder&); // NOLINT
1911 
1912  public:
1913  // cppcheck-suppress uninitMemberVar
1914  DOCTEST_NOINLINE ContextBuilder() // NOLINT
1915  : numCaptures(0)
1916  , head(0)
1917  , tail(0) {}
1918 
1919  template <typename T>
1920  DOCTEST_NOINLINE ContextBuilder& operator<<(T& in) {
1921  Capture<T> temp(&in);
1922 
1923  // construct either on stack or on heap
1924  // copy the bytes for the whole object - including the vtable because we cant construct
1925  // the object directly in the buffer using placement new - need the <new> header...
1926  if(numCaptures < DOCTEST_CONFIG_NUM_CAPTURES_ON_STACK) {
1927  my_memcpy(stackChunks[numCaptures].buf, &temp, sizeof(Chunk));
1928  } else {
1929  Node* curr = new Node;
1930  curr->next = 0;
1931  if(tail) {
1932  tail->next = curr;
1933  tail = curr;
1934  } else {
1935  head = tail = curr;
1936  }
1937 
1938  my_memcpy(tail->chunk.buf, &temp, sizeof(Chunk));
1939  }
1940  ++numCaptures;
1941  return *this;
1942  }
1943 
1944  DOCTEST_NOINLINE ~ContextBuilder() {
1945  // free the linked list - the ones on the stack are left as-is
1946  // no destructors are called at all - there is no need
1947  while(head) {
1948  Node* next = head->next;
1949  delete head;
1950  head = next;
1951  }
1952  }
1953 
1954 #ifdef DOCTEST_CONFIG_WITH_RVALUE_REFERENCES
1955  template <typename T>
1956  ContextBuilder& operator<<(const T&&) {
1957  DOCTEST_STATIC_ASSERT(
1958  deferred_false<T>::value,
1959  Cannot_pass_temporaries_or_rvalues_to_the_streaming_operator_because_it_caches_pointers_to_the_passed_objects_for_lazy_evaluation);
1960  return *this;
1961  }
1962 #endif // DOCTEST_CONFIG_WITH_RVALUE_REFERENCES
1963  };
1964 
1965  class ContextScope : public IContextScope
1966  {
1967  ContextBuilder contextBuilder;
1968  bool built;
1969 
1970  public:
1971  DOCTEST_NOINLINE explicit ContextScope(ContextBuilder& temp)
1972  : contextBuilder(temp)
1973  , built(false) {
1974  addToContexts(this);
1975  }
1976 
1977  DOCTEST_NOINLINE ~ContextScope() {
1978  if(!built)
1979  useContextIfExceptionOccurred(this);
1980  popFromContexts();
1981  }
1982 
1983  void build(std::ostream* stream) {
1984  built = true;
1985  contextBuilder.build(stream);
1986  }
1987  };

2442 #define DOCTEST_ASSERT_THROWS(expr, assert_type) \
2443  do { \
2444  if(!doctest::detail::getTestsContextState()->no_throw) { \
2445  doctest::detail::ResultBuilder _DOCTEST_RB(doctest::detail::assertType::assert_type, \
2446  __FILE__, __LINE__, #expr); \
2447  try { \
2448  expr; \
2449  } catch(...) { _DOCTEST_RB.m_threw = true; } \
2450  DOCTEST_ASSERT_LOG_AND_REACT(_DOCTEST_RB); \
2451  } \
2452  } while((void)0, 0)
2453 
2454 #define DOCTEST_ASSERT_THROWS_AS(expr, as, assert_type) \
2455  do { \
2456  if(!doctest::detail::getTestsContextState()->no_throw) { \
2457  doctest::detail::ResultBuilder _DOCTEST_RB( \
2458  doctest::detail::assertType::assert_type, __FILE__, __LINE__, #expr, \
2459  DOCTEST_TOSTR(DOCTEST_HANDLE_BRACED_VA_ARGS(as))); \
2460  try { \
2461  expr; \
2462  } catch(const DOCTEST_HANDLE_BRACED_VA_ARGS(as)&) { \
2463  _DOCTEST_RB.m_threw = true; \
2464  _DOCTEST_RB.m_threw_as = true; \
2465  } catch(...) { _DOCTEST_RB.unexpectedExceptionOccurred(); } \
2466  DOCTEST_ASSERT_LOG_AND_REACT(_DOCTEST_RB); \
2467  } \
2468  } while((void)0, 0)
2469 
2470 #define DOCTEST_ASSERT_NOTHROW(expr, assert_type) \

2473  doctest::detail::ResultBuilder _DOCTEST_RB(doctest::detail::assertType::assert_type, \
2474  __FILE__, __LINE__, #expr); \

2476  expr; \
2477  } catch(...) { _DOCTEST_RB.unexpectedExceptionOccurred(); } \
2478  DOCTEST_ASSERT_LOG_AND_REACT(_DOCTEST_RB); \
2479  } \
2480  } while((void)0, 0)

2514 #ifdef DOCTEST_CONFIG_WITH_VARIADIC_MACROS
2515 #define DOCTEST_BINARY_ASSERT(assert_type, expr, comp) \
2516  do { \
2517  doctest::detail::ResultBuilder _DOCTEST_RB( \
2518  doctest::detail::assertType::assert_type, __FILE__, __LINE__, \
2519  DOCTEST_TOSTR(DOCTEST_HANDLE_BRACED_VA_ARGS(expr))); \
2520  DOCTEST_WRAP_IN_TRY( \
2521  _DOCTEST_RB.binary_assert<doctest::detail::binaryAssertComparison::comp>( \
2522  DOCTEST_HANDLE_BRACED_VA_ARGS(expr))) \
2523  DOCTEST_ASSERT_LOG_AND_REACT(_DOCTEST_RB); \
2524  } while((void)0, 0)
2525 #else // DOCTEST_CONFIG_WITH_VARIADIC_MACROS
2526 #define DOCTEST_BINARY_ASSERT(assert_type, lhs, rhs, comp) \
2527  do { \
2528  doctest::detail::ResultBuilder _DOCTEST_RB(doctest::detail::assertType::assert_type, \
2529  __FILE__, __LINE__, #lhs ", " #rhs); \
2530  DOCTEST_WRAP_IN_TRY( \
2531  _DOCTEST_RB.binary_assert<doctest::detail::binaryAssertComparison::comp>(lhs, \
2532  rhs)) \
2533  DOCTEST_ASSERT_LOG_AND_REACT(_DOCTEST_RB); \
2534  } while((void)0, 0)
2535 #endif // DOCTEST_CONFIG_WITH_VARIADIC_MACROS

2541  DOCTEST_TOSTR(DOCTEST_HANDLE_BRACED_VA_ARGS(expr))); \
2542  DOCTEST_WRAP_IN_TRY(_DOCTEST_RB.unary_assert(DOCTEST_HANDLE_BRACED_VA_ARGS(expr))) \
2543  DOCTEST_ASSERT_LOG_AND_REACT(_DOCTEST_RB); \
2544  } while((void)0, 0)

2602 #ifdef DOCTEST_CONFIG_WITH_VARIADIC_MACROS
2603 #define DOCTEST_FAST_BINARY_ASSERT(assert_type, expr, comparison) \
2604  do { \
2605  int _DOCTEST_FAST_RES = doctest::detail::fast_binary_assert< \
2606  doctest::detail::binaryAssertComparison::comparison>( \
2607  doctest::detail::assertType::assert_type, __FILE__, __LINE__, \
2608  DOCTEST_TOSTR(DOCTEST_HANDLE_BRACED_VA_ARGS(expr)), \
2609  DOCTEST_HANDLE_BRACED_VA_ARGS(expr)); \
2610  if(_DOCTEST_FAST_RES & doctest::detail::assertAction::dbgbreak) \
2611  DOCTEST_BREAK_INTO_DEBUGGER(); \
2612  doctest::detail::fastAssertThrowIfFlagSet(_DOCTEST_FAST_RES); \
2613  } while((void)0, 0)
2614 #else // DOCTEST_CONFIG_WITH_VARIADIC_MACROS
2615 #define DOCTEST_FAST_BINARY_ASSERT(assert_type, lhs, rhs, comparison) \
2616  do { \
2617  int _DOCTEST_FAST_RES = doctest::detail::fast_binary_assert< \
2618  doctest::detail::binaryAssertComparison::comparison>( \
2619  doctest::detail::assertType::assert_type, __FILE__, __LINE__, #lhs ", " #rhs, lhs, \
2620  rhs); \
2621  if(_DOCTEST_FAST_RES & doctest::detail::assertAction::dbgbreak) \
2622  DOCTEST_BREAK_INTO_DEBUGGER(); \
2623  doctest::detail::fastAssertThrowIfFlagSet(_DOCTEST_FAST_RES); \
2624  } while((void)0, 0)
2625 #endif // DOCTEST_CONFIG_WITH_VARIADIC_MACROS

2800 #define DOCTEST_IMPLEMENT_FIXTURE(der, base, func, name) \
2801  namespace \
2802  { \
2803  template <typename DOCTEST_UNUSED_TEMPLATE_TYPE> \
2804  struct der : base \
2805  { void f(); }; \
2806  } \
2807  template <typename DOCTEST_UNUSED_TEMPLATE_TYPE> \
2808  inline void der<DOCTEST_UNUSED_TEMPLATE_TYPE>::f()
2809 
2810 #define DOCTEST_CREATE_AND_REGISTER_FUNCTION(f, name) \
2811  template <typename DOCTEST_UNUSED_TEMPLATE_TYPE> \
2812  static inline void f()
2813 
2814 // for registering tests
2815 #define DOCTEST_TEST_CASE(name) \
2816  DOCTEST_CREATE_AND_REGISTER_FUNCTION(DOCTEST_ANONYMOUS(_DOCTEST_ANON_FUNC_), name)
2817 
2818 // for registering tests with a fixture
2819 #define DOCTEST_TEST_CASE_FIXTURE(x, name) \
2820  DOCTEST_IMPLEMENT_FIXTURE(DOCTEST_ANONYMOUS(_DOCTEST_ANON_CLASS_), x, \
2821  DOCTEST_ANONYMOUS(_DOCTEST_ANON_FUNC_), name)

2826 #define DOCTEST_TYPE_TO_STRING_IMPL(...)
2827 #else // DOCTEST_CONFIG_WITH_VARIADIC_MACROS

2830 #endif // DOCTEST_CONFIG_WITH_VARIADIC_MACROS

2835  inline void DOCTEST_ANONYMOUS(_DOCTEST_ANON_TMP_)()
2836

2839  inline void DOCTEST_ANONYMOUS(_DOCTEST_ANON_TMP_)()
2840

3329  // lowers ascii letters
3330  char tolower(const char c) { return (c >= 'A' && c <= 'Z') ? static_cast<char>(c + 32) : c; }
3331 
3332  template <typename T>
3333  T my_max(const T& lhs, const T& rhs) {
3334  return lhs > rhs ? lhs : rhs;
3335  }
3336 
3337  // case insensitive strcmp
3338  int stricmp(char const* a, char const* b) {
3339  for(;; a++, b++) {
3340  const int d = tolower(*a) - tolower(*b);
3341  if(d != 0 || !*a)
3342  return d;
3343  }
3344  }

3346  void my_memcpy(void* dest, const void* src, unsigned num) {
3347  const char* csrc = static_cast<const char*>(src);
3348  char* cdest = static_cast<char*>(dest);
3349  for(unsigned i = 0; i < num; ++i)
3350  cdest[i] = csrc[i];
3351  }
3352 
3353  // not using std::strlen() because of valgrind errors when optimizations are turned on
3354  // 'Invalid read of size 4' when the test suite len (with '\0') is not a multiple of 4
3355  // for details see http://stackoverflow.com/questions/35671155
3356  unsigned my_strlen(const char* in) {
3357  const char* temp = in;
3358  while(temp && *temp)
3359  ++temp;
3360  return unsigned(temp - in);
3361  }

3363  template <typename T>
3364  String fpToString(T value, int precision) {
3365  std::ostringstream oss;
3366  oss << std::setprecision(precision) << std::fixed << value;
3367  std::string d = oss.str();
3368  size_t i = d.find_last_not_of('0');
3369  if(i != std::string::npos && i != d.size() - 1) {
3370  if(d[i] == '.')
3371  i++;
3372  d = d.substr(0, i + 1);
3373  }
3374  return d.c_str();
3375  }

3377  struct Endianness
3378  {
3379  enum Arch
3380  {
3381  Big,
3382  Little
3383  };
3384 
3385  static Arch which() {
3386  union _
3387  {
3388  int asInt;
3389  char asChar[sizeof(int)];
3390  } u;
3391 
3392  u.asInt = 1; // NOLINT
3393  return (u.asChar[sizeof(int) - 1] == 1) ? Big : Little; // NOLINT
3394  }
3395  };
3396 
3397  String rawMemoryToString(const void* object, unsigned size) {
3398  // Reverse order for little endian architectures
3399  int i = 0, end = static_cast<int>(size), inc = 1;
3400  if(Endianness::which() == Endianness::Little) {
3401  i = end - 1;
3402  end = inc = -1;
3403  }
3404 
3405  unsigned char const* bytes = static_cast<unsigned char const*>(object);
3406  std::ostringstream os;
3407  os << "0x" << std::setfill('0') << std::hex;
3408  for(; i != end; i += inc)
3409  os << std::setw(2) << static_cast<unsigned>(bytes[i]);
3410  return os.str().c_str();
3411  }

3500 void String::copy(const String& other) {
3501  if(other.isOnStack()) {
3502  detail::my_memcpy(buf, other.buf, len);
3503  } else {
3504  setOnHeap();
3505  data.size = other.data.size;
3506  data.capacity = data.size + 1;
3507  data.ptr = new char[data.capacity];
3508  detail::my_memcpy(data.ptr, other.data.ptr, data.size + 1);
3509  }
3510 }
3511 
3512 String::String(const char* in) {
3513  unsigned in_len = detail::my_strlen(in);
3514  if(in_len <= last) {
3515  detail::my_memcpy(buf, in, in_len + 1);
3516  setLast(last - in_len);
3517  } else {
3518  setOnHeap();
3519  data.size = in_len;
3520  data.capacity = data.size + 1;
3521  data.ptr = new char[data.capacity];
3522  detail::my_memcpy(data.ptr, in, in_len + 1);
3523  }
3524 }
3525 
3526 String& String::operator+=(const String& other) {
3527  const unsigned my_old_size = size();
3528  const unsigned other_size = other.size();
3529  const unsigned total_size = my_old_size + other_size;
3530  if(isOnStack()) {
3531  if(total_size < len) {
3532  // append to the current stack space
3533  detail::my_memcpy(buf + my_old_size, other.c_str(), other_size + 1);
3534  setLast(last - total_size);
3535  } else {
3536  // alloc new chunk
3537  char* temp = new char[total_size + 1];
3538  // copy current data to new location before writing in the union
3539  detail::my_memcpy(temp, buf, my_old_size); // skip the +1 ('\0') for speed
3540  // update data in union
3541  setOnHeap();
3542  data.size = total_size;
3543  data.capacity = data.size + 1;
3544  data.ptr = temp;
3545  // transfer the rest of the data
3546  detail::my_memcpy(data.ptr + my_old_size, other.c_str(), other_size + 1);
3547  }
3548  } else {
3549  if(data.capacity > total_size) {
3550  // append to the current heap block
3551  data.size = total_size;
3552  detail::my_memcpy(data.ptr + my_old_size, other.c_str(), other_size + 1);
3553  } else {
3554  // resize
3555  data.capacity *= 2;
3556  if(data.capacity <= total_size)
3557  data.capacity = total_size + 1;
3558  // alloc new chunk
3559  char* temp = new char[data.capacity];
3560  // copy current data to new location before releasing it
3561  detail::my_memcpy(temp, data.ptr, my_old_size); // skip the +1 ('\0') for speed
3562  // release old chunk
3563  delete[] data.ptr;
3564  // update the rest of the union members
3565  data.size = total_size;
3566  data.ptr = temp;
3567  // transfer the rest of the data
3568  detail::my_memcpy(data.ptr + my_old_size, other.c_str(), other_size + 1);
3569  }
3570  }
3571 
3572  return *this;
3573 }
3574

3576 String::String(String&& other) {
3577  detail::my_memcpy(buf, other.buf, len);
3578  other.buf[0] = '\0';
3579  other.setLast();
3580 }

3582 String& String::operator=(String&& other) {
3583  if(this != &other) {
3584  if(!isOnStack())
3585  delete[] data.ptr;
3586  detail::my_memcpy(buf, other.buf, len);
3587  other.buf[0] = '\0';
3588  other.setLast();
3589  }
3590  return *this;
3591 }
3592 #endif // DOCTEST_CONFIG_WITH_RVALUE_REFERENCES

3609 Approx::Approx(double value)
3610  : m_epsilon(static_cast<double>(std::numeric_limits<float>::epsilon()) * 100)
3611  , m_scale(1.0)
3612  , m_value(value) {}
3613 
3614 bool operator==(double lhs, Approx const& rhs) {
3615  // Thanks to Richard Harris for his help refining this formula
3616  return std::fabs(lhs - rhs.m_value) <
3617  rhs.m_epsilon * (rhs.m_scale + detail::my_max(std::fabs(lhs), std::fabs(rhs.m_value)));
3618 }

3816  TestCase& TestCase::operator*(const char* in) {
3817  m_name = in;
3818  // make a new name with an appended type for templated test case
3819  if(m_template_id != -1) {
3820  m_full_name = String(m_name) + m_type;
3821  // redirect the name to point to the newly constructed full name
3822  m_name = m_full_name.c_str();
3823  }
3824  return *this;
3825  }

3848  bool TestCase::operator<(const TestCase& other) const {

3850  return m_line < other.m_line;

3852  if(file_cmp != 0)
3853  return file_cmp < 0;
3854  return m_template_id < other.m_template_id;

3939  bool checkIfShouldThrow(assertType::Enum assert_type) {

3942

3944  && contextState->abort_after > 0 &&
3945  contextState->numFailedAssertions >= contextState->abort_after)
3946  return true;
3947 
3948  return false;
3949  }

3960  // matching of a string against a wildcard mask (case sensitivity configurable) taken from
3961  // http://www.emoticode.net/c/simple-wildcard-string-compare-globbing-function.html
3962  int wildcmp(const char* str, const char* wild, bool caseSensitive) {
3963  const char* cp = 0;
3964  const char* mp = 0;
3965 
3966  // rolled my own tolower() to not include more headers
3967  while((*str) && (*wild != '*')) {
3968  if((caseSensitive ? (*wild != *str) : (tolower(*wild) != tolower(*str))) &&
3969  (*wild != '?')) {
3970  return 0;
3971  }
3972  wild++;
3973  str++;
3974  }
3975 
3976  while(*str) {
3977  if(*wild == '*') {
3978  if(!*++wild) {
3979  return 1;
3980  }
3981  mp = wild;
3982  cp = str + 1;
3983  } else if((caseSensitive ? (*wild == *str) : (tolower(*wild) == tolower(*str))) ||
3984  (*wild == '?')) {
3985  wild++;
3986  str++;
3987  } else {
3988  wild = mp;
3989  str = cp++;
3990  }
3991  }
3992 
3993  while(*wild == '*') {
3994  wild++;
3995  }
3996  return !*wild;
3997  }

4001  // unsigned long hash = 5381;
4002  // char c;
4003  // while((c = *str++))
4004  // hash = ((hash << 5) + hash) + c; // hash * 33 + c
4005  // return hash;
4006  //}
4007 
4008  // checks if the name matches any of the filters (and can be configured what to do when empty)
4009  bool matchesAny(const char* name, const std::vector<String>& filters, int matchEmpty,
4010  bool caseSensitive) {
4011  if(filters.empty() && matchEmpty)
4012  return true;
4013  for(unsigned i = 0; i < filters.size(); ++i)
4014  if(wildcmp(name, filters[i].c_str(), caseSensitive))
4015  return true;
4016  return false;
4017  }

4019 #ifdef DOCTEST_PLATFORM_WINDOWS
4020 
4021  typedef unsigned long long UInt64;
4022 
4023  UInt64 getCurrentTicks() {
4024  static UInt64 hz = 0, hzo = 0;
4025  if(!hz) {
4026  QueryPerformanceFrequency(reinterpret_cast<LARGE_INTEGER*>(&hz));
4027  QueryPerformanceCounter(reinterpret_cast<LARGE_INTEGER*>(&hzo));
4028  }
4029  UInt64 t;
4030  QueryPerformanceCounter(reinterpret_cast<LARGE_INTEGER*>(&t));
4031  return ((t - hzo) * 1000000) / hz;
4032  }
4033 #else // DOCTEST_PLATFORM_WINDOWS
4034 
4035  typedef uint64_t UInt64;
4036 
4037  UInt64 getCurrentTicks() {
4038  timeval t;
4039  gettimeofday(&t, 0);
4040  return static_cast<UInt64>(t.tv_sec) * 1000000 + static_cast<UInt64>(t.tv_usec);
4041  }
4042 #endif // DOCTEST_PLATFORM_WINDOWS

4044  class Timer
4045  {
4046  public:
4047  Timer()
4048  : m_ticks(0) {}
4049  void start() { m_ticks = getCurrentTicks(); }
4050  unsigned int getElapsedMicroseconds() const {
4051  return static_cast<unsigned int>(getCurrentTicks() - m_ticks);
4052  }
4053  unsigned int getElapsedMilliseconds() const {
4054  return static_cast<unsigned int>(getElapsedMicroseconds() / 1000);
4055  }
4056  double getElapsedSeconds() const { return getElapsedMicroseconds() / 1000000.0; }
4057 
4058  private:
4059  UInt64 m_ticks;
4060  };

4064  bool SubcaseSignature::operator<(const SubcaseSignature& other) const {
4065  if(m_line != other.m_line)
4066  return m_line < other.m_line;
4067  if(std::strcmp(m_file, other.m_file) != 0)
4068  return std::strcmp(m_file, other.m_file) < 0;
4069  return std::strcmp(m_name, other.m_name) < 0;
4070  }
4071 
4072  Subcase::Subcase(const char* name, const char* file, int line)
4073  : m_signature(name, file, line)
4074  , m_entered(false) {
4075  ContextState* s = contextState;
4076 
4077  // if we have already completed it
4078  if(s->subcasesPassed.count(m_signature) != 0)
4079  return;
4080 
4081  // check subcase filters
4082  if(s->subcasesCurrentLevel < s->subcase_filter_levels) {
4083  if(!matchesAny(m_signature.m_name, s->filters[6], 1, s->case_sensitive))
4084  return;
4085  if(matchesAny(m_signature.m_name, s->filters[7], 0, s->case_sensitive))
4086  return;
4087  }
4088 
4089  // if a Subcase on the same level has already been entered
4090  if(s->subcasesEnteredLevels.count(s->subcasesCurrentLevel) != 0) {
4091  s->subcasesHasSkipped = true;
4092  return;
4093  }
4094 
4095  s->subcasesStack.push_back(*this);
4096  if(s->hasLoggedCurrentTestStart)
4097  logTestEnd();
4098  s->hasLoggedCurrentTestStart = false;
4099 
4100  s->subcasesEnteredLevels.insert(s->subcasesCurrentLevel++);
4101  m_entered = true;
4102  }
4103 
4104  Subcase::Subcase(const Subcase& other)
4105  : m_signature(other.m_signature.m_name, other.m_signature.m_file,
4106  other.m_signature.m_line)
4107  , m_entered(other.m_entered) {}
4108 
4109  Subcase::~Subcase() {
4110  if(m_entered) {
4111  ContextState* s = contextState;
4112 
4113  s->subcasesCurrentLevel--;
4114  // only mark the subcase as passed if no subcases have been skipped
4115  if(s->subcasesHasSkipped == false)
4116  s->subcasesPassed.insert(m_signature);
4117 
4118  if(!s->subcasesStack.empty())
4119  s->subcasesStack.pop_back();
4120  if(s->hasLoggedCurrentTestStart)
4121  logTestEnd();
4122  s->hasLoggedCurrentTestStart = false;
4123  }
4124  }

4135  // for sorting tests by file/line
4136  int fileOrderComparator(const void* a, const void* b) {
4137  const TestCase* lhs = *static_cast<TestCase* const*>(a);
4138  const TestCase* rhs = *static_cast<TestCase* const*>(b);
4139 #if DOCTEST_MSVC
4140  // this is needed because MSVC gives different case for drive letters
4141  // for __FILE__ when evaluated in a header and a source file
4142  const int res = stricmp(lhs->m_file, rhs->m_file);
4143 #else // MSVC
4144  const int res = std::strcmp(lhs->m_file, rhs->m_file);
4145 #endif // MSVC
4146  if(res != 0)
4147  return res;
4148  return static_cast<int>(lhs->m_line - rhs->m_line);
4149  }
4150 
4151  // for sorting tests by suite/file/line
4152  int suiteOrderComparator(const void* a, const void* b) {
4153  const TestCase* lhs = *static_cast<TestCase* const*>(a);
4154  const TestCase* rhs = *static_cast<TestCase* const*>(b);
4155 
4156  const int res = std::strcmp(lhs->m_test_suite, rhs->m_test_suite);
4157  if(res != 0)
4158  return res;
4159  return fileOrderComparator(a, b);
4160  }
4161 
4162  // for sorting tests by name/suite/file/line
4163  int nameOrderComparator(const void* a, const void* b) {
4164  const TestCase* lhs = *static_cast<TestCase* const*>(a);
4165  const TestCase* rhs = *static_cast<TestCase* const*>(b);
4166 
4167  const int res_name = std::strcmp(lhs->m_name, rhs->m_name);
4168  if(res_name != 0)
4169  return res_name;
4170  return suiteOrderComparator(a, b);
4171  }

4225  void Color::init() {

4227  if(!g_attrsInitted) {
4228  g_stdoutHandle = GetStdHandle(STD_OUTPUT_HANDLE);
4229  g_attrsInitted = true;
4230  CONSOLE_SCREEN_BUFFER_INFO csbiInfo;
4231  GetConsoleScreenBufferInfo(g_stdoutHandle, &csbiInfo);
4232  g_originalForegroundAttributes =
4233  csbiInfo.wAttributes &
4234  ~(BACKGROUND_GREEN | BACKGROUND_RED | BACKGROUND_BLUE | BACKGROUND_INTENSITY);
4235  g_originalBackgroundAttributes =
4236  csbiInfo.wAttributes &
4237  ~(FOREGROUND_GREEN | FOREGROUND_RED | FOREGROUND_BLUE | FOREGROUND_INTENSITY);
4238  }
4239 #endif // DOCTEST_CONFIG_COLORS_WINDOWS
4240  }
4241 
4242  void Color::use(Code
4243 #ifndef DOCTEST_CONFIG_COLORS_NONE
4244  code
4245 #endif // DOCTEST_CONFIG_COLORS_NONE
4246  ) {
4247  const ContextState* p = contextState;
4248  if(p->no_colors)
4249  return;
4250 #ifdef DOCTEST_CONFIG_COLORS_ANSI
4251  if(isatty(STDOUT_FILENO) == false && p->force_colors == false)
4252  return;
4253 
4254  const char* col = "";
4255  // clang-format off
4256  switch(code) {
4257  case Color::Red: col = "[0;31m"; break;
4258  case Color::Green: col = "[0;32m"; break;
4259  case Color::Blue: col = "[0;34m"; break;
4260  case Color::Cyan: col = "[0;36m"; break;
4261  case Color::Yellow: col = "[0;33m"; break;
4262  case Color::Grey: col = "[1;30m"; break;
4263  case Color::LightGrey: col = "[0;37m"; break;
4264  case Color::BrightRed: col = "[1;31m"; break;
4265  case Color::BrightGreen: col = "[1;32m"; break;
4266  case Color::BrightWhite: col = "[1;37m"; break;
4267  case Color::Bright: // invalid
4268  case Color::None:
4269  case Color::White:
4270  default: col = "[0m";
4271  }
4272  // clang-format on
4273  std::printf("\033%s", col);
4274 #endif // DOCTEST_CONFIG_COLORS_ANSI
4275 
4276 #ifdef DOCTEST_CONFIG_COLORS_WINDOWS
4277  if(isatty(fileno(stdout)) == false && p->force_colors == false)
4278  return;
4279 
4280 #define DOCTEST_SET_ATTR(x) \
4281  SetConsoleTextAttribute(g_stdoutHandle, x | g_originalBackgroundAttributes)
4282 
4283  // clang-format off
4284  switch (code) {
4285  case Color::White: DOCTEST_SET_ATTR(FOREGROUND_GREEN | FOREGROUND_RED | FOREGROUND_BLUE); break;
4286  case Color::Red: DOCTEST_SET_ATTR(FOREGROUND_RED); break;
4287  case Color::Green: DOCTEST_SET_ATTR(FOREGROUND_GREEN); break;
4288  case Color::Blue: DOCTEST_SET_ATTR(FOREGROUND_BLUE); break;
4289  case Color::Cyan: DOCTEST_SET_ATTR(FOREGROUND_BLUE | FOREGROUND_GREEN); break;
4290  case Color::Yellow: DOCTEST_SET_ATTR(FOREGROUND_RED | FOREGROUND_GREEN); break;
4291  case Color::Grey: DOCTEST_SET_ATTR(0); break;
4292  case Color::LightGrey: DOCTEST_SET_ATTR(FOREGROUND_INTENSITY); break;
4293  case Color::BrightRed: DOCTEST_SET_ATTR(FOREGROUND_INTENSITY | FOREGROUND_RED); break;
4294  case Color::BrightGreen: DOCTEST_SET_ATTR(FOREGROUND_INTENSITY | FOREGROUND_GREEN); break;
4295  case Color::BrightWhite: DOCTEST_SET_ATTR(FOREGROUND_INTENSITY | FOREGROUND_GREEN | FOREGROUND_RED | FOREGROUND_BLUE); break;
4296  case Color::None:
4297  case Color::Bright: // invalid
4298  default: DOCTEST_SET_ATTR(g_originalForegroundAttributes);
4299  }
4300 // clang-format on
4301 #undef DOCTEST_SET_ATTR
4302 #endif // DOCTEST_CONFIG_COLORS_WINDOWS
4303  }

4312  translateFunction) == getExceptionTranslators().end())

4316  String translateActiveException() {
4317 #ifndef DOCTEST_CONFIG_NO_EXCEPTIONS
4318  String res;
4319  std::vector<const IExceptionTranslator*>& translators = getExceptionTranslators();
4320  for(size_t i = 0; i < translators.size(); ++i)
4321  if(translators[i]->translate(res))
4322  return res;
4323  // clang-format off
4324  try {
4325  throw;
4326  } catch(std::exception& ex) {
4327  return ex.what();
4328  } catch(std::string& msg) {
4329  return msg.c_str();
4330  } catch(const char* msg) {
4331  return msg;
4332  } catch(...) {
4333  return "unknown exception";
4334  }
4335 // clang-format on
4336 #else // DOCTEST_CONFIG_NO_EXCEPTIONS
4337  return "";
4338 #endif // DOCTEST_CONFIG_NO_EXCEPTIONS
4339  }

4391  void reportFatal(const std::string& message) {
4392  DOCTEST_LOG_START();

4394  contextState->numAssertions += contextState->numAssertionsForCurrentTestcase;
4395  logTestException(message.c_str(), true);

4402 #ifdef DOCTEST_PLATFORM_WINDOWS
4403 
4404  struct SignalDefs
4405  {
4406  DWORD id;
4407  const char* name;
4408  };
4409  // There is no 1-1 mapping between signals and windows exceptions.
4410  // Windows can easily distinguish between SO and SigSegV,
4411  // but SigInt, SigTerm, etc are handled differently.
4412  SignalDefs signalDefs[] = {
4413  {EXCEPTION_ILLEGAL_INSTRUCTION, "SIGILL - Illegal instruction signal"},
4414  {EXCEPTION_STACK_OVERFLOW, "SIGSEGV - Stack overflow"},
4415  {EXCEPTION_ACCESS_VIOLATION, "SIGSEGV - Segmentation violation signal"},
4416  {EXCEPTION_INT_DIVIDE_BY_ZERO, "Divide by zero error"},
4417  };
4418 
4419  struct FatalConditionHandler
4420  {
4421  static LONG CALLBACK handleVectoredException(PEXCEPTION_POINTERS ExceptionInfo) {
4422  for(size_t i = 0; i < sizeof(signalDefs) / sizeof(SignalDefs); ++i) {
4423  if(ExceptionInfo->ExceptionRecord->ExceptionCode == signalDefs[i].id) {
4424  reportFatal(signalDefs[i].name);
4425  }
4426  }
4427  // If its not an exception we care about, pass it along.
4428  // This stops us from eating debugger breaks etc.
4429  return EXCEPTION_CONTINUE_SEARCH;
4430  }
4431 
4432  FatalConditionHandler() {
4433  isSet = true;
4434  // 32k seems enough for doctest to handle stack overflow,
4435  // but the value was found experimentally, so there is no strong guarantee
4436  guaranteeSize = 32 * 1024;
4437  exceptionHandlerHandle = 0;
4438  // Register as first handler in current chain
4439  exceptionHandlerHandle = AddVectoredExceptionHandler(1, handleVectoredException);
4440  // Pass in guarantee size to be filled
4441  SetThreadStackGuarantee(&guaranteeSize);
4442  }
4443 
4444  static void reset() {
4445  if(isSet) {
4446  // Unregister handler and restore the old guarantee
4447  RemoveVectoredExceptionHandler(exceptionHandlerHandle);
4448  SetThreadStackGuarantee(&guaranteeSize);
4449  exceptionHandlerHandle = 0;
4450  isSet = false;
4451  }
4452  }
4453 
4454  ~FatalConditionHandler() { reset(); }
4455 
4456  private:
4457  static bool isSet;
4458  static ULONG guaranteeSize;
4459  static PVOID exceptionHandlerHandle;
4460  };
4461 
4462  bool FatalConditionHandler::isSet = false;
4463  ULONG FatalConditionHandler::guaranteeSize = 0;
4464  PVOID FatalConditionHandler::exceptionHandlerHandle = 0;
4465 
4466 #else // DOCTEST_PLATFORM_WINDOWS
4467 
4468  struct SignalDefs
4469  {
4470  int id;
4471  const char* name;
4472  };
4473  SignalDefs signalDefs[] = {{SIGINT, "SIGINT - Terminal interrupt signal"},
4474  {SIGILL, "SIGILL - Illegal instruction signal"},
4475  {SIGFPE, "SIGFPE - Floating point error signal"},
4476  {SIGSEGV, "SIGSEGV - Segmentation violation signal"},
4477  {SIGTERM, "SIGTERM - Termination request signal"},
4478  {SIGABRT, "SIGABRT - Abort (abnormal termination) signal"}};
4479 
4480  struct FatalConditionHandler
4481  {
4482  static bool isSet;
4483  static struct sigaction oldSigActions[sizeof(signalDefs) / sizeof(SignalDefs)];
4484  static stack_t oldSigStack;
4485  static char altStackMem[SIGSTKSZ];
4486 
4487  static void handleSignal(int sig) {
4488  std::string name = "<unknown signal>";
4489  for(std::size_t i = 0; i < sizeof(signalDefs) / sizeof(SignalDefs); ++i) {
4490  SignalDefs& def = signalDefs[i];
4491  if(sig == def.id) {
4492  name = def.name;
4493  break;
4494  }
4495  }
4496  reset();
4497  reportFatal(name);
4498  raise(sig);
4499  }
4500 
4501  FatalConditionHandler() {
4502  isSet = true;
4503  stack_t sigStack;
4504  sigStack.ss_sp = altStackMem;
4505  sigStack.ss_size = SIGSTKSZ;
4506  sigStack.ss_flags = 0;
4507  sigaltstack(&sigStack, &oldSigStack);
4508  struct sigaction sa = {0};
4509 
4510  sa.sa_handler = handleSignal; // NOLINT
4511  sa.sa_flags = SA_ONSTACK;
4512  for(std::size_t i = 0; i < sizeof(signalDefs) / sizeof(SignalDefs); ++i) {
4513  sigaction(signalDefs[i].id, &sa, &oldSigActions[i]);
4514  }
4515  }
4516 
4517  ~FatalConditionHandler() { reset(); }
4518  static void reset() {
4519  if(isSet) {
4520  // Set signals back to previous values -- hopefully nobody overwrote them in the meantime
4521  for(std::size_t i = 0; i < sizeof(signalDefs) / sizeof(SignalDefs); ++i) {
4522  sigaction(signalDefs[i].id, &oldSigActions[i], 0);
4523  }
4524  // Return the old stack
4525  sigaltstack(&oldSigStack, 0);
4526  isSet = false;
4527  }
4528  }
4529  };
4530 
4531  bool FatalConditionHandler::isSet = false;
4532  struct sigaction FatalConditionHandler::oldSigActions[sizeof(signalDefs) / sizeof(SignalDefs)] =
4533  {};
4534  stack_t FatalConditionHandler::oldSigStack = {};
4535  char FatalConditionHandler::altStackMem[SIGSTKSZ] = {};
4536 
4537 #endif // DOCTEST_PLATFORM_WINDOWS
4538 #endif // DOCTEST_CONFIG_POSIX_SIGNALS || DOCTEST_CONFIG_WINDOWS_SEH

4540  // depending on the current options this will remove the path of filenames
4541  const char* fileForOutput(const char* file) {
4542  if(contextState->no_path_in_filenames) {
4543  const char* back = std::strrchr(file, '\\');
4544  const char* forward = std::strrchr(file, '/');
4545  if(back || forward) {
4546  if(back > forward)
4547  forward = back;
4548  return forward + 1;
4549  }
4550  }
4551  return file;
4552  }
4553 
4554  // depending on the current options this will substitute the line numbers with 0
4555  int lineForOutput(int line) {
4556  if(contextState->no_line_numbers)
4557  return 0;
4558  return line;
4559  }
4560 
4561 #ifdef DOCTEST_PLATFORM_MAC
4562 #include <sys/types.h>
4563 #include <unistd.h>
4564 #include <sys/sysctl.h>
4565  // The following function is taken directly from the following technical note:
4566  // http://developer.apple.com/library/mac/#qa/qa2004/qa1361.html
4567  // Returns true if the current process is being debugged (either
4568  // running under the debugger or has a debugger attached post facto).
4569  bool isDebuggerActive() {
4570  int mib[4];
4571  kinfo_proc info;
4572  size_t size;
4573  // Initialize the flags so that, if sysctl fails for some bizarre
4574  // reason, we get a predictable result.
4575  info.kp_proc.p_flag = 0;
4576  // Initialize mib, which tells sysctl the info we want, in this case
4577  // we're looking for information about a specific process ID.
4578  mib[0] = CTL_KERN;
4579  mib[1] = KERN_PROC;
4580  mib[2] = KERN_PROC_PID;
4581  mib[3] = getpid();
4582  // Call sysctl.
4583  size = sizeof(info);
4584  if(sysctl(mib, sizeof(mib) / sizeof(*mib), &info, &size, 0, 0) != 0) {
4585  fprintf(stderr, "\n** Call to sysctl failed - unable to determine if debugger is "
4586  "active **\n\n");
4587  return false;
4588  }
4589  // We're being debugged if the P_TRACED flag is set.
4590  return ((info.kp_proc.p_flag & P_TRACED) != 0);
4591  }
4592 #elif DOCTEST_MSVC || defined(__MINGW32__)
4593  bool isDebuggerActive() { return ::IsDebuggerPresent() != 0; }
4594 #else
4595  bool isDebuggerActive() { return false; }
4596 #endif // Platform
4597

4599  void myOutputDebugString(const String& text) { ::OutputDebugStringA(text.c_str()); }
4600 #else
4601  // TODO: integration with XCode and other IDEs
4602  void myOutputDebugString(const String&) {}
4603 #endif // Platform

4610  if(isDebuggerActive())
4611  myOutputDebugString(text.c_str());
4612  }

4622  void logTestStart(const TestCase& tc) {
4623  char loc[DOCTEST_SNPRINTF_BUFFER_LENGTH];
4624  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(loc, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(loc), "%s(%d)\n", fileForOutput(tc.m_file),
4625  lineForOutput(tc.m_line));
4626 
4627  char ts1[DOCTEST_SNPRINTF_BUFFER_LENGTH];
4628  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(ts1, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(ts1), "TEST SUITE: ");
4629  char ts2[DOCTEST_SNPRINTF_BUFFER_LENGTH];
4630  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(ts2, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(ts2), "%s\n", tc.m_test_suite);
4631  char n1[DOCTEST_SNPRINTF_BUFFER_LENGTH];
4632  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(n1, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(n1), "TEST CASE: ");
4633  char n2[DOCTEST_SNPRINTF_BUFFER_LENGTH];
4634  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(n2, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(n2), "%s\n", tc.m_name);
4635  char d1[DOCTEST_SNPRINTF_BUFFER_LENGTH];
4636  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(d1, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(d1), "DESCRIPTION: ");
4637  char d2[DOCTEST_SNPRINTF_BUFFER_LENGTH];
4638  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(d2, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(d2), "%s\n", tc.m_description);
4639 
4640  // hack for BDD style of macros - to not print "TEST CASE:"
4641  char scenario[] = " Scenario:";
4642  if(std::string(tc.m_name).substr(0, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(scenario) - 1) == scenario)
4643  n1[0] = '\0';
4644 
4645  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(getSeparator(), Color::Yellow);
4646  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(loc, Color::LightGrey);
4647 
4648  String forDebugConsole;
4649  if(tc.m_description) {
4650  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(d1, Color::Yellow);
4651  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(d2, Color::None);
4652  forDebugConsole += d1;
4653  forDebugConsole += d2;
4654  }
4655  if(tc.m_test_suite && tc.m_test_suite[0] != '\0') {
4656  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(ts1, Color::Yellow);
4657  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(ts2, Color::None);
4658  forDebugConsole += ts1;
4659  forDebugConsole += ts2;
4660  }
4661  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(n1, Color::Yellow);
4662  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(n2, Color::None);
4663 
4664  String subcaseStuff;
4665  std::vector<Subcase>& subcasesStack = contextState->subcasesStack;
4666  for(unsigned i = 0; i < subcasesStack.size(); ++i) {
4667  if(subcasesStack[i].m_signature.m_name[0] != '\0') {
4668  char subcase[DOCTEST_SNPRINTF_BUFFER_LENGTH];
4669  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(subcase, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(loc), " %s\n",
4670  subcasesStack[i].m_signature.m_name);
4671  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(subcase, Color::None);
4672  subcaseStuff += subcase;
4673  }
4674  }
4675 
4676  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED("\n", Color::None);
4677 
4678  printToDebugConsole(String(getSeparator()) + loc + forDebugConsole.c_str() + n1 + n2 +
4679  subcaseStuff.c_str() + "\n");
4680  }

4684  void logTestException(const String& what, bool crash) {
4685  char msg[DOCTEST_SNPRINTF_BUFFER_LENGTH];
4686 
4687  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(msg, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(msg), "TEST CASE FAILED!\n");
4688 
4689  char info1[DOCTEST_SNPRINTF_BUFFER_LENGTH];
4690  char info2[DOCTEST_SNPRINTF_BUFFER_LENGTH];
4691  info1[0] = 0;
4692  info2[0] = 0;
4693  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(info1, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(info1),
4694  crash ? "crashed:\n" : "threw exception:\n");
4695  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(info2, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(info2), " %s\n", what.c_str());
4696 
4697  std::string contextStr;
4698 
4699  if(!contextState->exceptionalContexts.empty()) {
4700  contextStr += "with context:\n";
4701  for(size_t i = contextState->exceptionalContexts.size(); i > 0; --i) {
4702  contextStr += " ";
4703  contextStr += contextState->exceptionalContexts[i - 1];
4704  contextStr += "\n";
4705  }
4706  }
4707 
4708  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(msg, Color::Red);
4709  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(info1, Color::None);
4710  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(info2, Color::Cyan);
4711  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(contextStr.c_str(), Color::None);
4712  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED("\n", Color::None);
4713 
4714  printToDebugConsole(String(msg) + info1 + info2 + contextStr.c_str() + "\n");
4715  }

4717  String logContext() {
4718  std::ostringstream stream;
4719  std::vector<IContextScope*>& contexts = contextState->contexts;
4720  if(!contexts.empty())
4721  stream << "with context:\n";
4722  for(size_t i = 0; i < contexts.size(); ++i) {
4723  stream << " ";
4724  contexts[i]->build(&stream);
4725  stream << "\n";
4726  }
4727  return stream.str().c_str();
4728  }

4730  const char* getFailString(assertType::Enum assert_type) {
4731  if(assert_type & assertType::is_warn)
4732  return "WARNING";
4733  if(assert_type & assertType::is_check)
4734  return "ERROR";
4735  if(assert_type & assertType::is_require)
4736  return "FATAL ERROR";
4737  return "";
4738  }

4740  void logAssert(bool passed, const char* decomposition, bool threw, const String& exception,
4741  const char* expr, assertType::Enum assert_type, const char* file, int line) {
4742  char loc[DOCTEST_SNPRINTF_BUFFER_LENGTH];
4743  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(loc, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(loc), "%s(%d)", fileForOutput(file),
4744  lineForOutput(line));
4745 
4746  char msg[DOCTEST_SNPRINTF_BUFFER_LENGTH];
4747  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(msg, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(msg), " %s!\n",
4748  passed ? "PASSED" : getFailString(assert_type));
4749 
4750  char info1[DOCTEST_SNPRINTF_BUFFER_LENGTH];
4751  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(info1, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(info1), " %s( %s )\n",
4752  getAssertString(assert_type), expr);
4753 
4754  char info2[DOCTEST_SNPRINTF_BUFFER_LENGTH];
4755  char info3[DOCTEST_SNPRINTF_BUFFER_LENGTH];
4756  info2[0] = 0;
4757  info3[0] = 0;
4758  if(threw) {
4759  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(info2, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(info2), "threw exception:\n");
4760  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(info3, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(info3), " %s\n", exception.c_str());
4761  } else {
4762  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(info2, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(info2), "with expansion:\n");
4763  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(info3, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(info3), " %s( %s )\n",
4764  getAssertString(assert_type), decomposition);
4765  }

4767  const bool isWarn = assert_type & assertType::is_warn;
4768  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(loc, Color::LightGrey);

4771  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(info1, Color::Cyan);
4772  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(info2, Color::None);
4773  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(info3, Color::Cyan);
4774  String context = logContext();
4775  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(context.c_str(), Color::None);
4776  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED("\n", Color::None);
4777

4802  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(loc, Color::LightGrey);

4915 
4916  bool ResultBuilder::log() {
4917  if((m_assert_type & assertType::is_warn) == 0)
4918  contextState->numAssertionsForCurrentTestcase++;
4919 
4920  if(m_assert_type & assertType::is_throws) {
4921  m_failed = !m_threw;
4922  } else if(m_assert_type &
4923  assertType::is_throws_as) {
4924  m_failed = !m_threw_as;
4925  } else if(m_assert_type &
4926  assertType::is_nothrow) {
4927  m_failed = m_threw;
4928  } else {
4929  m_failed = m_result;
4930  }
4931 
4932  if(m_failed || contextState->success) {
4933  DOCTEST_LOG_START();
4934 
4935  if(m_assert_type & assertType::is_throws) {
4936  logAssertThrows(m_threw, m_expr, m_assert_type, m_file, m_line);
4937  } else if(m_assert_type &
4938  assertType::is_throws_as) {
4939  logAssertThrowsAs(m_threw, m_threw_as, m_exception_type, m_exception, m_expr,
4940  m_assert_type, m_file, m_line);
4941  } else if(m_assert_type &
4942  assertType::is_nothrow) {
4943  logAssertNothrow(m_threw, m_exception, m_expr, m_assert_type, m_file, m_line);
4944  } else {
4945  logAssert(m_result.m_passed, m_result.m_decomposition.c_str(), m_threw, m_exception,
4946  m_expr, m_assert_type, m_file, m_line);
4947  }
4948  }
4949 
4950  if(m_failed)
4951  addFailedAssert(m_assert_type);
4952 
4953  return m_failed && isDebuggerActive() && !contextState->no_breaks; // break into debugger
4954  }
4955 
4956  void ResultBuilder::react() const {
4957  if(m_failed && checkIfShouldThrow(m_assert_type))
4958  throwException();
4959  }

4962  : m_stream(createStream())
4963  , m_file(file)
4964  , m_line(line)
4965  , m_severity(severity) {}
4966 
4967  bool MessageBuilder::log() {
4968  DOCTEST_LOG_START();
4969 
4970  const bool isWarn = m_severity & assertType::is_warn;
4971 
4972  // warn is just a message in this context so we dont treat it as an assert
4973  if(!isWarn) {
4974  contextState->numAssertionsForCurrentTestcase++;
4975  addFailedAssert(m_severity);
4976  }
4977 
4978  char loc[DOCTEST_SNPRINTF_BUFFER_LENGTH];
4979  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(loc, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(loc), "%s(%d)", fileForOutput(m_file),
4980  lineForOutput(m_line));
4981  char msg[DOCTEST_SNPRINTF_BUFFER_LENGTH];
4982  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(msg, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(msg), " %s!\n",
4983  isWarn ? "MESSAGE" : getFailString(m_severity));
4984 
4985  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(loc, Color::LightGrey);
4986  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(msg, isWarn ? Color::Yellow : Color::Red);
4987 
4988  String info = getStreamResult(m_stream);
4989  if(info.size()) {
4990  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(" ", Color::None);
4991  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(info.c_str(), Color::None);
4992  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED("\n", Color::None);
4993  }
4994  String context = logContext();
4995  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(context.c_str(), Color::None);
4996  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED("\n", Color::None);
4997 
4998  printToDebugConsole(String(loc) + msg + " " + info.c_str() + "\n" + context.c_str() +
4999  "\n");
5000 
5001  return isDebuggerActive() && !contextState->no_breaks && !isWarn; // break into debugger
5002  }

5010 
5011  // the implementation of parseFlag()
5012  bool parseFlagImpl(int argc, const char* const* argv, const char* pattern) {
5013  for(int i = argc - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
5014  const char* temp = std::strstr(argv[i], pattern);
5015  if(temp && my_strlen(temp) == my_strlen(pattern)) {
5016  // eliminate strings in which the chars before the option are not '-'
5017  bool noBadCharsFound = true;
5018  while(temp != argv[i]) {
5019  if(*--temp != '-') {
5020  noBadCharsFound = false;
5021  break;
5022  }
5023  }
5024  if(noBadCharsFound && argv[i][0] == '-')
5025  return true;
5026  }
5027  }
5028  return false;
5029  }
5030 
5031  // locates a flag on the command line
5032  bool parseFlag(int argc, const char* const* argv, const char* pattern) {
5033 #ifndef DOCTEST_CONFIG_NO_UNPREFIXED_OPTIONS
5034  if(!parseFlagImpl(argc, argv, pattern))
5035  return parseFlagImpl(argc, argv, pattern + 3); // 3 for "dt-"
5036  return true;
5037 #else // DOCTEST_CONFIG_NO_UNPREFIXED_OPTIONS
5038  return parseFlagImpl(argc, argv, pattern);
5039 #endif // DOCTEST_CONFIG_NO_UNPREFIXED_OPTIONS
5040  }
5041 
5042  // the implementation of parseOption()
5043  bool parseOptionImpl(int argc, const char* const* argv, const char* pattern, String& res) {
5044  for(int i = argc - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
5045  const char* temp = std::strstr(argv[i], pattern);
5046  if(temp) {
5047  // eliminate matches in which the chars before the option are not '-'
5048  bool noBadCharsFound = true;
5049  const char* curr = argv[i];
5050  while(curr != temp) {
5051  if(*curr++ != '-') {
5052  noBadCharsFound = false;
5053  break;
5054  }
5055  }
5056  if(noBadCharsFound && argv[i][0] == '-') {
5057  temp += my_strlen(pattern);
5058  const unsigned len = my_strlen(temp);
5059  if(len) {
5060  res = temp;
5061  return true;
5062  }
5063  }
5064  }
5065  }
5066  return false;
5067  }
5068 
5069  // parses an option and returns the string after the '=' character
5070  bool parseOption(int argc, const char* const* argv, const char* pattern, String& res,
5071  const String& defaultVal = String()) {
5072  res = defaultVal;
5073 #ifndef DOCTEST_CONFIG_NO_UNPREFIXED_OPTIONS
5074  if(!parseOptionImpl(argc, argv, pattern, res))
5075  return parseOptionImpl(argc, argv, pattern + 3, res); // 3 for "dt-"
5076  return true;
5077 #else // DOCTEST_CONFIG_NO_UNPREFIXED_OPTIONS
5078  return parseOptionImpl(argc, argv, pattern, res);
5079 #endif // DOCTEST_CONFIG_NO_UNPREFIXED_OPTIONS
5080  }
5081 
5082  // parses a comma separated list of words after a pattern in one of the arguments in argv
5083  bool parseCommaSepArgs(int argc, const char* const* argv, const char* pattern,
5084  std::vector<String>& res) {
5085  String filtersString;
5086  if(parseOption(argc, argv, pattern, filtersString)) {
5087  // tokenize with "," as a separator
5088  // cppcheck-suppress strtokCalled
5089  char* pch = std::strtok(filtersString.c_str(), ","); // modifies the string
5090  while(pch != 0) {
5091  if(my_strlen(pch))
5092  res.push_back(pch);
5093  // uses the strtok() internal state to go to the next token
5094  // cppcheck-suppress strtokCalled
5095  pch = std::strtok(0, ",");
5096  }
5097  return true;
5098  }
5099  return false;
5100  }
5101 
5102  enum optionType
5103  {
5104  option_bool,
5105  option_int
5106  };
5107 
5108  // parses an int/bool option from the command line
5109  bool parseIntOption(int argc, const char* const* argv, const char* pattern, optionType type,
5110  int& res) {
5111  String parsedValue;
5112  if(!parseOption(argc, argv, pattern, parsedValue))
5113  return false;
5114 
5115  if(type == 0) {
5116  // boolean
5117  const char positive[][5] = {"1", "true", "on", "yes"}; // 5 - strlen("true") + 1
5118  const char negative[][6] = {"0", "false", "off", "no"}; // 6 - strlen("false") + 1
5119 
5120  // if the value matches any of the positive/negative possibilities
5121  for(unsigned i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
5122  if(parsedValue.compare(positive[i], true) == 0) {
5123  res = 1;
5124  return true;
5125  }
5126  if(parsedValue.compare(negative[i], true) == 0) {
5127  res = 0;
5128  return true;
5129  }
5130  }
5131  } else {
5132  // integer
5133  int theInt = std::atoi(parsedValue.c_str()); // NOLINT
5134  if(theInt != 0) {
5135  res = theInt;
5136  return true;
5137  }
5138  }
5139  return false;
5140  }

5216  void printSummary() {
5217  const ContextState* p = contextState;
5218 
5219  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(getSeparator(), Color::Yellow);
5220  if(p->count || p->list_test_cases) {
5221  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED("[doctest] ", Color::Cyan);
5222  std::printf("unskipped test cases passing the current filters: %u\n",
5223  p->numTestsPassingFilters);
5224  } else if(p->list_test_suites) {
5225  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED("[doctest] ", Color::Cyan);
5226  std::printf("unskipped test cases passing the current filters: %u\n",
5227  p->numTestsPassingFilters);
5228  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED("[doctest] ", Color::Cyan);
5229  std::printf("test suites with unskipped test cases passing the current filters: %u\n",
5230  p->numTestSuitesPassingFilters);
5231  } else {
5232  const bool anythingFailed = p->numFailed > 0 || p->numFailedAssertions > 0;
5233 
5234  char buff[DOCTEST_SNPRINTF_BUFFER_LENGTH];
5235 
5236  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED("[doctest] ", Color::Cyan);
5237 
5238  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(buff, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(buff), "test cases: %6u",
5239  p->numTestsPassingFilters);
5240  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(buff, Color::None);
5241  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(buff, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(buff), " | ");
5242  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(buff, Color::None);
5243  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(buff, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(buff), "%6u passed",
5244  p->numTestsPassingFilters - p->numFailed);
5245  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(buff, (p->numTestsPassingFilters == 0 || anythingFailed) ?
5246  Color::None :
5247  Color::Green);
5248  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(buff, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(buff), " | ");
5249  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(buff, Color::None);
5250  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(buff, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(buff), "%6u failed", p->numFailed);
5251  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(buff, p->numFailed > 0 ? Color::Red : Color::None);
5252 
5253  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(buff, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(buff), " | ");
5254  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(buff, Color::None);
5255  if(p->no_skipped_summary == false) {
5256  const int numSkipped = static_cast<unsigned>(getRegisteredTests().size()) -
5257  p->numTestsPassingFilters;
5258  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(buff, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(buff), "%6d skipped", numSkipped);
5259  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(buff, numSkipped == 0 ? Color::None : Color::Yellow);
5260  }
5261  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED("\n", Color::None);
5262 
5263  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED("[doctest] ", Color::Cyan);
5264 
5265  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(buff, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(buff), "assertions: %6d", p->numAssertions);
5266  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(buff, Color::None);
5267  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(buff, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(buff), " | ");
5268  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(buff, Color::None);
5269  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(buff, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(buff), "%6d passed",
5270  p->numAssertions - p->numFailedAssertions);
5271  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(buff, (p->numAssertions == 0 || anythingFailed) ? Color::None :
5272  Color::Green);
5273  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(buff, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(buff), " | ");
5274  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(buff, Color::None);
5275  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(buff, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(buff), "%6d failed", p->numFailedAssertions);
5276  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(buff, p->numFailedAssertions > 0 ? Color::Red : Color::None);
5277 
5278  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(buff, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(buff), " |\n");
5279  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(buff, Color::None);
5280 
5281  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED("[doctest] ", Color::Cyan);
5282  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED("Status: ", Color::None);
5283  const char* result = (p->numFailed > 0) ? "FAILURE!\n" : "SUCCESS!\n";
5284  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(result, p->numFailed > 0 ? Color::Red : Color::Green);
5285  }
5286 
5287  // remove any coloring
5288  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED("", Color::None);
5289  }
5290 } // namespace detail

5292 bool isRunningInTest() { return detail::contextState != 0; }
