5303 // parses args
5304 void Context::parseArgs(int argc, const char* const* argv, bool withDefaults) {
5305  using namespace detail;
5306 
5307  // clang-format off
5308  parseCommaSepArgs(argc, argv, "dt-source-file=", p->filters[0]);
5309  parseCommaSepArgs(argc, argv, "dt-sf=", p->filters[0]);
5310  parseCommaSepArgs(argc, argv, "dt-source-file-exclude=",p->filters[1]);
5311  parseCommaSepArgs(argc, argv, "dt-sfe=", p->filters[1]);
5312  parseCommaSepArgs(argc, argv, "dt-test-suite=", p->filters[2]);
5313  parseCommaSepArgs(argc, argv, "dt-ts=", p->filters[2]);
5314  parseCommaSepArgs(argc, argv, "dt-test-suite-exclude=", p->filters[3]);
5315  parseCommaSepArgs(argc, argv, "dt-tse=", p->filters[3]);
5316  parseCommaSepArgs(argc, argv, "dt-test-case=", p->filters[4]);
5317  parseCommaSepArgs(argc, argv, "dt-tc=", p->filters[4]);
5318  parseCommaSepArgs(argc, argv, "dt-test-case-exclude=", p->filters[5]);
5319  parseCommaSepArgs(argc, argv, "dt-tce=", p->filters[5]);
5320  parseCommaSepArgs(argc, argv, "dt-subcase=", p->filters[6]);
5321  parseCommaSepArgs(argc, argv, "dt-sc=", p->filters[6]);
5322  parseCommaSepArgs(argc, argv, "dt-subcase-exclude=", p->filters[7]);
5323  parseCommaSepArgs(argc, argv, "dt-sce=", p->filters[7]);
5324  // clang-format on
5325 
5326  int intRes = 0;
5327  String strRes;
5328 
5329 #define DOCTEST_PARSE_AS_BOOL_OR_FLAG(name, sname, var, default) \
5330  if(parseIntOption(argc, argv, name "=", option_bool, intRes) || \
5331  parseIntOption(argc, argv, sname "=", option_bool, intRes)) \
5332  p->var = !!intRes; \
5333  else if(parseFlag(argc, argv, name) || parseFlag(argc, argv, sname)) \
5334  p->var = true; \
5335  else if(withDefaults) \
5336  p->var = default
5337 
5338 #define DOCTEST_PARSE_INT_OPTION(name, sname, var, default) \
5339  if(parseIntOption(argc, argv, name "=", option_int, intRes) || \
5340  parseIntOption(argc, argv, sname "=", option_int, intRes)) \
5341  p->var = intRes; \
5342  else if(withDefaults) \
5343  p->var = default
5344 
5345 #define DOCTEST_PARSE_STR_OPTION(name, sname, var, default) \
5346  if(parseOption(argc, argv, name "=", strRes, default) || \
5347  parseOption(argc, argv, sname "=", strRes, default) || withDefaults) \
5348  p->var = strRes
5349 
5350  // clang-format off
5351  DOCTEST_PARSE_STR_OPTION("dt-order-by", "dt-ob", order_by, "file");
5352  DOCTEST_PARSE_INT_OPTION("dt-rand-seed", "dt-rs", rand_seed, 0);
5353 
5354  DOCTEST_PARSE_INT_OPTION("dt-first", "dt-f", first, 1);
5355  DOCTEST_PARSE_INT_OPTION("dt-last", "dt-l", last, 0);
5356 
5357  DOCTEST_PARSE_INT_OPTION("dt-abort-after", "dt-aa", abort_after, 0);
5358  DOCTEST_PARSE_INT_OPTION("dt-subcase-filter-levels", "dt-scfl", subcase_filter_levels, 2000000000);
5359 
5360  DOCTEST_PARSE_AS_BOOL_OR_FLAG("dt-success", "dt-s", success, false);
5361  DOCTEST_PARSE_AS_BOOL_OR_FLAG("dt-case-sensitive", "dt-cs", case_sensitive, false);
5362  DOCTEST_PARSE_AS_BOOL_OR_FLAG("dt-exit", "dt-e", exit, false);
5363  DOCTEST_PARSE_AS_BOOL_OR_FLAG("dt-duration", "dt-d", duration, false);
5364  DOCTEST_PARSE_AS_BOOL_OR_FLAG("dt-no-throw", "dt-nt", no_throw, false);
5365  DOCTEST_PARSE_AS_BOOL_OR_FLAG("dt-no-exitcode", "dt-ne", no_exitcode, false);
5366  DOCTEST_PARSE_AS_BOOL_OR_FLAG("dt-no-run", "dt-nr", no_run, false);
5367  DOCTEST_PARSE_AS_BOOL_OR_FLAG("dt-no-version", "dt-nv", no_version, false);
5368  DOCTEST_PARSE_AS_BOOL_OR_FLAG("dt-no-colors", "dt-nc", no_colors, false);
5369  DOCTEST_PARSE_AS_BOOL_OR_FLAG("dt-force-colors", "dt-fc", force_colors, false);
5370  DOCTEST_PARSE_AS_BOOL_OR_FLAG("dt-no-breaks", "dt-nb", no_breaks, false);
5371  DOCTEST_PARSE_AS_BOOL_OR_FLAG("dt-no-skip", "dt-ns", no_skip, false);
5372  DOCTEST_PARSE_AS_BOOL_OR_FLAG("dt-no-path-filenames", "dt-npf", no_path_in_filenames, false);
5373  DOCTEST_PARSE_AS_BOOL_OR_FLAG("dt-no-line-numbers", "dt-nln", no_line_numbers, false);
5374  DOCTEST_PARSE_AS_BOOL_OR_FLAG("dt-no-skipped-summary", "dt-nss", no_skipped_summary, false);
5375  // clang-format on
5376 
5377 #undef DOCTEST_PARSE_STR_OPTION
5378 #undef DOCTEST_PARSE_INT_OPTION
5379 #undef DOCTEST_PARSE_AS_BOOL_OR_FLAG
5380 
5381  if(withDefaults) {
5382  p->help = false;
5383  p->version = false;
5384  p->count = false;
5385  p->list_test_cases = false;
5386  p->list_test_suites = false;
5387  }
5388  if(parseFlag(argc, argv, "dt-help") || parseFlag(argc, argv, "dt-h") ||
5389  parseFlag(argc, argv, "dt-?")) {
5390  p->help = true;
5391  p->exit = true;
5392  }
5393  if(parseFlag(argc, argv, "dt-version") || parseFlag(argc, argv, "dt-v")) {
5394  p->version = true;
5395  p->exit = true;
5396  }
5397  if(parseFlag(argc, argv, "dt-count") || parseFlag(argc, argv, "dt-c")) {
5398  p->count = true;
5399  p->exit = true;
5400  }
5401  if(parseFlag(argc, argv, "dt-list-test-cases") || parseFlag(argc, argv, "dt-ltc")) {
5402  p->list_test_cases = true;
5403  p->exit = true;
5404  }
5405  if(parseFlag(argc, argv, "dt-list-test-suites") || parseFlag(argc, argv, "dt-lts")) {
5406  p->list_test_suites = true;
5407  p->exit = true;
5408  }
5409 }

5411 // allows the user to add procedurally to the filters from the command line

5413 
5414 // allows the user to clear all filters from the command line
5415 void Context::clearFilters() {
5416  for(unsigned i = 0; i < p->filters.size(); ++i)
5417  p->filters[i].clear();
5418 }

5420 // allows the user to override procedurally the int/bool options from the command line
5421 void Context::setOption(const char* option, int value) {
5422  setOption(option, toString(value).c_str());
5423 }
5424 
5425 // allows the user to override procedurally the string options from the command line
5426 void Context::setOption(const char* option, const char* value) {
5427  String argv = String("-") + option + "=" + value;
5428  const char* lvalue = argv.c_str();
5429  parseArgs(1, &lvalue);
5430 }

5432 // users should query this in their main() and exit the program if true
5433 bool Context::shouldExit() { return p->exit; }
5434 
5435 // the main function that does all the filtering and test running
5436 int Context::run() {
5437  using namespace detail;
5438 
5439  Color::init();
5440 
5441  contextState = p;
5442  p->resetRunData();
5443 
5444  // handle version, help and no_run
5445  if(p->no_run || p->version || p->help) {
5446  if(p->version)
5447  printVersion();
5448  if(p->help)
5449  printHelp();
5450 
5451  contextState = 0;
5452 
5453  return EXIT_SUCCESS;
5454  }
5455 
5456  printVersion();
5457  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED("[doctest] ", Color::Cyan);
5458  std::printf("run with \"--help\" for options\n");
5459 
5460  unsigned i = 0; // counter used for loops - here for VC6
5461 
5462  std::set<TestCase>& registeredTests = getRegisteredTests();
5463 
5464  std::vector<const TestCase*> testArray;
5465  for(std::set<TestCase>::iterator it = registeredTests.begin(); it != registeredTests.end();
5466  ++it)
5467  testArray.push_back(&(*it));
5468 
5469  // sort the collected records
5470  if(!testArray.empty()) {
5471  if(p->order_by.compare("file", true) == 0) {
5472  std::qsort(&testArray[0], testArray.size(), sizeof(TestCase*), fileOrderComparator);
5473  } else if(p->order_by.compare("suite", true) == 0) {
5474  std::qsort(&testArray[0], testArray.size(), sizeof(TestCase*), suiteOrderComparator);
5475  } else if(p->order_by.compare("name", true) == 0) {
5476  std::qsort(&testArray[0], testArray.size(), sizeof(TestCase*), nameOrderComparator);
5477  } else if(p->order_by.compare("rand", true) == 0) {
5478  std::srand(p->rand_seed);
5479 
5480  // random_shuffle implementation
5481  const TestCase** first = &testArray[0];
5482  for(i = testArray.size() - 1; i > 0; --i) {
5483  int idxToSwap = std::rand() % (i + 1); // NOLINT
5484 
5485  const TestCase* temp = first[i];
5486 
5487  first[i] = first[idxToSwap];
5488  first[idxToSwap] = temp;
5489  }
5490  }
5491  }
5492 
5493  if(p->list_test_cases) {
5494  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED("[doctest] ", Color::Cyan);
5495  std::printf("listing all test case names\n");
5496  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(getSeparator(), Color::Yellow);
5497  }
5498 
5499  std::set<String> testSuitesPassingFilters;
5500  if(p->list_test_suites) {
5501  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED("[doctest] ", Color::Cyan);
5502  std::printf("listing all test suites\n");
5503  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(getSeparator(), Color::Yellow);
5504  }
5505 
5506  // invoke the registered functions if they match the filter criteria (or just count them)
5507  for(i = 0; i < testArray.size(); i++) {
5508  const TestCase& data = *testArray[i];
5509 
5510  if(data.m_skip && !p->no_skip)
5511  continue;
5512 
5513  if(!matchesAny(data.m_file, p->filters[0], 1, p->case_sensitive))
5514  continue;
5515  if(matchesAny(data.m_file, p->filters[1], 0, p->case_sensitive))
5516  continue;
5517  if(!matchesAny(data.m_test_suite, p->filters[2], 1, p->case_sensitive))
5518  continue;
5519  if(matchesAny(data.m_test_suite, p->filters[3], 0, p->case_sensitive))
5520  continue;
5521  if(!matchesAny(data.m_name, p->filters[4], 1, p->case_sensitive))
5522  continue;
5523  if(matchesAny(data.m_name, p->filters[5], 0, p->case_sensitive))
5524  continue;
5525 
5526  p->numTestsPassingFilters++;
5527 
5528  // do not execute the test if we are to only count the number of filter passing tests
5529  if(p->count)
5530  continue;
5531 
5532  // print the name of the test and don't execute it
5533  if(p->list_test_cases) {
5534  std::printf("%s\n", data.m_name);
5535  continue;
5536  }
5537 
5538  // print the name of the test suite if not done already and don't execute it
5539  if(p->list_test_suites) {
5540  if((testSuitesPassingFilters.count(data.m_test_suite) == 0) &&
5541  data.m_test_suite[0] != '\0') {
5542  std::printf("%s\n", data.m_test_suite);
5543  testSuitesPassingFilters.insert(data.m_test_suite);
5544  p->numTestSuitesPassingFilters++;
5545  }
5546  continue;
5547  }
5548 
5549  // skip the test if it is not in the execution range
5550  if((p->last < p->numTestsPassingFilters && p->first <= p->last) ||
5551  (p->first > p->numTestsPassingFilters))
5552  continue;
5553 
5554  // execute the test if it passes all the filtering
5555  {
5556  p->currentTest = &data;
5557 
5558  bool failed = false;
5559  p->hasLoggedCurrentTestStart = false;
5560  p->numFailedAssertionsForCurrentTestcase = 0;
5561  p->subcasesPassed.clear();
5562  double duration = 0;
5563  Timer timer;
5564  timer.start();
5565  do {
5566  // if the start has been logged from a previous iteration of this loop
5567  if(p->hasLoggedCurrentTestStart)
5568  logTestEnd();
5569  p->hasLoggedCurrentTestStart = false;
5570 
5571  // if logging successful tests - force the start log
5572  if(p->success)
5573  DOCTEST_LOG_START();
5574 
5575  // reset the assertion state
5576  p->numAssertionsForCurrentTestcase = 0;
5577  p->hasCurrentTestFailed = false;
5578 
5579  // reset some of the fields for subcases (except for the set of fully passed ones)
5580  p->subcasesHasSkipped = false;
5581  p->subcasesCurrentLevel = 0;
5582  p->subcasesEnteredLevels.clear();
5583 
5584  // reset stuff for logging with INFO()
5585  p->exceptionalContexts.clear();
5586 
5587 // execute the test
5588 #ifndef DOCTEST_CONFIG_NO_EXCEPTIONS
5589  try {
5590 #endif // DOCTEST_CONFIG_NO_EXCEPTIONS
5591  FatalConditionHandler fatalConditionHandler; // Handle signals
5592  data.m_test();
5593  fatalConditionHandler.reset();
5594  if(contextState->hasCurrentTestFailed)
5595  failed = true;
5596 #ifndef DOCTEST_CONFIG_NO_EXCEPTIONS
5597  } catch(const TestFailureException&) { failed = true; } catch(...) {
5598  DOCTEST_LOG_START();
5599  logTestException(translateActiveException());
5600  failed = true;
5601  }
5602 #endif // DOCTEST_CONFIG_NO_EXCEPTIONS
5603 
5604  p->numAssertions += p->numAssertionsForCurrentTestcase;
5605 
5606  // exit this loop if enough assertions have failed
5607  if(p->abort_after > 0 && p->numFailedAssertions >= p->abort_after) {
5608  p->subcasesHasSkipped = false;
5609  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED("Aborting - too many failed asserts!\n", Color::Red);
5610  }
5611 
5612  } while(p->subcasesHasSkipped == true);
5613 
5614  duration = timer.getElapsedSeconds();
5615 
5616  if(Approx(p->currentTest->m_timeout).epsilon(DBL_EPSILON) != 0 &&
5617  Approx(duration).epsilon(DBL_EPSILON) > p->currentTest->m_timeout) {
5618  failed = true;
5619  DOCTEST_LOG_START();
5620  char msg[DOCTEST_SNPRINTF_BUFFER_LENGTH];
5621  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(msg, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(msg),
5622  "Test case exceeded time limit of %.6f!\n",
5623  p->currentTest->m_timeout);
5624  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(msg, Color::Red);
5625  }
5626 
5627  if(p->duration) {
5628  char msg[DOCTEST_SNPRINTF_BUFFER_LENGTH];
5629  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(msg, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(msg), "%.6f s: %s\n", duration,
5630  p->currentTest->m_name);
5631  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(msg, Color::None);
5632  }
5633 
5634  if(data.m_should_fail) {
5635  DOCTEST_LOG_START();
5636  if(failed) {
5637  failed = false;
5638  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED("Failed as expected so marking it as not failed\n",
5639  Color::Yellow);
5640  } else {
5641  failed = true;
5642  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED("Should have failed but didn't! Marking it as failed!\n",
5643  Color::Red);
5644  }
5645  } else if(failed && data.m_may_fail) {
5646  DOCTEST_LOG_START();
5647  failed = false;
5648  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED("Allowed to fail so marking it as not failed\n",
5649  Color::Yellow);
5650  } else if(data.m_expected_failures > 0) {
5651  DOCTEST_LOG_START();
5652  char msg[DOCTEST_SNPRINTF_BUFFER_LENGTH];
5653  if(p->numFailedAssertionsForCurrentTestcase == data.m_expected_failures) {
5654  failed = false;
5655  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(
5656  msg, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(msg),
5657  "Failed exactly %d times as expected so marking it as not failed!\n",
5658  data.m_expected_failures);
5659  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(msg, Color::Yellow);
5660  } else {
5661  failed = true;
5662  DOCTEST_SNPRINTF(msg, DOCTEST_COUNTOF(msg),
5663  "Didn't fail exactly %d times so marking it as failed!\n",
5664  data.m_expected_failures);
5665  DOCTEST_PRINTF_COLORED(msg, Color::Red);
5666  }
5667  }
5668 
5669  if(p->hasLoggedCurrentTestStart)
5670  logTestEnd();
5671 
5672  if(failed) // if any subcase has failed - the whole test case has failed
5673  p->numFailed++;
5674 
5675  // stop executing tests if enough assertions have failed
5676  if(p->abort_after > 0 && p->numFailedAssertions >= p->abort_after)
5677  break;
5678  }
5679  }
5680 
5681  printSummary();
5682 
5683  contextState = 0;
5684 
5685  if(p->numFailed && !p->no_exitcode)
5686  return EXIT_FAILURE;
5687  return EXIT_SUCCESS;
5688 }
5689 } // namespace doctest
5690 
5691 #endif // DOCTEST_CONFIG_DISABLE
5692 
5693 #ifdef DOCTEST_CONFIG_IMPLEMENT_WITH_MAIN
5694 int main(int argc, char** argv) { return doctest::Context(argc, argv).run(); }
5695 #endif // DOCTEST_CONFIG_IMPLEMENT_WITH_MAIN
